%20mild%20surge%20of%200.7%20percent%2C%20while%20the%20US%20witnessed%20growth%20at%2018.9%20percent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECanada%20has%20been%20the%20primary%20choice%20for%20Indian%20students%20in%20three%20out%20of%20the%20last%20four%20years%2C%20with%20the%20US%20securing%20the%20top%20spot%20in%202021.%20Australia%20held%20the%20third%20position%2C%20and%20the%20UK%20was%20fourth%20in%202019%2C%202020%2C%20and%202021-a%20ranking%20that%20shifted%20in%202022.%20In%202022%2C%20Canada%20exhibited%20the%20highest%20year-on-year%20growth%20rate%2C%20indicating%20a%20surge%20in%20demand%20in%20the%20student%20mobility%20market%20following%20potential%20drops%20due%20to%20the%20Covid-19%20pandemic%20in%20previous%20years.%20Concerns%20about%20diplomatic%20tensions%20between%20India%20and%20Canada%20potentially%20affecting%20projections%20have%20been%20raised%2C%20with%20the%20suggestion%20that%20student%20interest%20may%20remain%20largely%20unaffected.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%20five%20years%20(since%202018)%2C%20Canada%20has%20augmented%20its%20intake%20from%20India%20by%20over%2086%25%2C%20almost%20doubling%20its%20numbers.%20Projections%20indicate%20a%20potential%20slight%20decline%20in%20momentum%20for%20Canada%20in%20the%20coming%20years.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Australia's%20standing%20as%20a%20top%20international%20student%20destination%20has%20gradually%20diminished%20over%20the%20past%20five%20years.%20Although%20it%20held%20the%20second%20position%20until%202019%20for%20total%20international%20students%2C%20it%20slipped%20to%20the%20fourth%20spot%20in%202021.%20Concerning%20Indian%20students%20heading%20to%20Australia%2C%20it%20descended%20to%20the%20third%20spot%20in%202019%20and%20further%20to%20the%20fourth%20place%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThree%20Core%20Matrices%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20introduces%20three%20fundamental%20matrices%20crafted%20to%20provide%20a%20comprehensive%20understanding%20of%20the%20Indian%20student's%20journey%20within%20the%20study%20abroad%20ecosystem.%20These%20matrices%20function%20as%20strategic%20tools%20for%20educational%20institutions%2C%20policymakers%2C%20and%20students%20alike%2C%20offering%20actionable%20insights%20into%20overseas%20education.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESpending%20on%20study%20abroad%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20reveals%20that%20nearly%208.5%20lakh%20students%20are%20pursuing%20higher%20education%20abroad%20in%20just%20four%20countries%20-%20the%20US%2C%20UK%2C%20Australia%2C%20and%20Canada%20-%20collectively%20spending%20close%20to%20US%24%2034%20billion%20in%202023.%20The%20detailed%20breakdown%20by%20country%20is%20as%20follows%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EUnited%20States%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndian%20students%2C%20numbering%20around%202%2C40%2C000%2C%20significantly%20contribute%20to%20the%20US%20economy%2C%20with%20a%20total%20expenditure%20of%20US%20%2412.48%20billion%20(approx%20%E2%82%B992%2C976%20crore).%20This%20includes%20US%20%247.2%20billion%20(approx%20%E2%82%B953%2C712%20crore)%20towards%20academic%20fees%2C%20US%20%242.9%20billion%20(approx%20%E2%82%B921%2C648%20crore)%20for%20accommodation%2C%20and%20US%20%242.4%20billion%20(approximately%20%E2%82%B917%2C712%20crore)%20on%20other%20living%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECanada%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Canada%2C%20Indian%20students%2C%20around%203%2C00%2C000%2C%20have%20an%20estimated%20total%20expenditure%20of%20US%20%2411.7%20billion%20(approx%20Rs%2087%2C036%20crore).%20This%20includes%20US%20%246%20billion%20(approx%20Rs%2044%2C712%20crore)%20on%20academic%20fees%2C%20US%20%243%20billion%20(approx%20Rs%2022%2C356%20crore)%20for%20accommodation%2C%20and%20US%20%242.7%20billion%20(approx%20Rs%2020%2C028%20crore)%20on%20other%20living%20necessities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAustralia%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndian%20students%2C%20approximately%