20of%20state%20had%20been%20advocating%20stronger%20US-India%20ties%20for%20the%20last%20one%20decade%20under%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsidered%20the%20architect%20of%20the%20US-China%20relationship%20since%20the%20early%2070s%2C%20Kissinger%20died%20at%20his%20home%20in%20Connecticut%20today.%20His%20consulting%20firm%2C%20Kissinger%20Associates%2C%20did%20not%20provide%20a%20cause%20of%20his%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20Narendra%20Modi%20became%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20of%20India%20in%202014%2C%20Kissinger%2C%20also%20the%20former%20US%20National%20Security%20Adviser%2C%20has%20been%20advocating%20strong%20ties%20with%20India.%20In%20fact%2C%20many%20say%2C%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years%20he%20has%20become%20a%20great%20fan%20of%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20PM%20Modi%20was%20in%20the%20US%20on%20an%20Official%20State%20Visit%20in%20June%20this%20year%2C%20Kissinger%20despite%20not%20keeping%20good%20health%2C%20travelled%20to%20Washington%20to%20listen%20to%20Narendra%20Modi's%20address%20at%20the%20luncheon%20at%20the%20State%20Department%20jointly%20hosted%20by%20Vice%20President%20Kamala%20Harris%20and%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Antony%20Blinken.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHenry%20Kissinger%20was%20brought%20in%20a%20wheelchair%20to%20the%20historic%20Benjamin%20Franklin%20Room%20on%20the%20seventh%20floor%20of%20the%20Foggy%20Bottom%20headquarters%20of%20the%20State%20Department.%20He%20was%20greeted%20at%20the%20elevator%20by%20US%20Ambassador%20to%20India%2C%20Eric%20Garcetti.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20luncheon%2C%20the%20elderly%20American%20statesman%2C%20whose%20influence%20on%20American%20national%20security%20and%20foreign%20policy%20is%20seen%20as%20immense%2C%20patiently%20listened%20to%20the%20speech%20of%20the%20prime%20minister%20and%20had%20an%20interaction%20with%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20recent%20years%2C%20Kissinger%20made%20his%20views%20known%20to%20the%20public%20on%20India%20when%20he%20made%20a%20fireside%20appearance%20in%20June%202018%20along%20with%20John%20Chambers%20of%20the%20US%20India%20Strategic%20and%20Partnership%20Forum%20(USISPF)%20on%20the%20occasion%20of%20the%20organisation's%20first%20anniversary.%20The%20fireside%20chat%20was%20closed%20to%20the%20press%2C%20but%20those%20who%20attended%20it%20recollect%20how%20strongly%20he%20batted%20for%20the%20India-US%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20I%20think%20about%20India%2C%20I%20admire%20their%20strategy%2C%26quot%3B%20Kissinger%20said%20during%20a%20rare%20appearance%20in%20Washington%20to%20attend%20the%20first%20annual%20leadership%20summit%20of%20the%20USISPF%20in%20June%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20ties%20with%20India%20in%20the%201970s%20when%20he%20was%20in%20the%20administration%20both%20as%20the%20National%20Security%20Advisor%20and%20Secretary%20of%20State%20had%20soured%2C%20but%20before%20he%20turned%20to%20China%2C%20his%20first%20preference%20was%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20at%20his%20advice%20that%20the%20US%20Chambers%20of%20Commerce%20in%20the%2070s%20established%20the%20US%20India%20Business%20Council%20(USIBC).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20archival%20diplomatic%20conversations%2C%20as%20early%20as%201972%20he%20had%20advocated%20for%20India%20and%20Japan%20to%20be%20the%20permanent%20member%20of%20the%20UN%20Security%20Council.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHistorians%20say%20that%20both%20Kissinger%20and%20then-President%20Richard%20Nixon%20could%20not%20have%20a%20healthy%20relationship%20with%20the%20then-Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20Indira%20Gandhi%20and%20they%20turned%20their%20attention%20to%20China.%20Rest%20is%20history%2C%20many%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20end%20of%20the%20Cold%20War%2C%20and%20the%20emergence%20of%20India%20as%20a%20strong%20power%20in%20the%20last%2010%20decades%2C%20his%20views%20on%20India%20had%20changed%20and%20for%20successive%20administrations%2C%20Kissinger%20has%20been%20advocating%20strong%20ties%20with%20India.%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20has%20had%20a%20few%20meetings%20with%20him%20during%20his%20trip%20to%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20at%20another%20USISPF%20event%2C%20Kissinger%2C%20then%2096%2C%20said%20the%20Bangladesh%20crisis%20pushed%20the%20two%20countries%20to%20the%20%26quot%3Bedge%20of%20confrontations''.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIndia%20was%20at%20the%20beginning%20of%20a%20historic%20evolution%20and%20not%20all%20of%20the%20problems%20that%20concerned%20were%20of%20equal%20importance%20to%20India.%20India%20was%20heavily%20involved%20with%20its%20own%20evolution%20and%20the%20policy%20of%20neutrality%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20then%20said%20in%20New%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20look%20at%20the%20world%2C%20there%20are%20upheavals%20in%20almost%20every%20part%20of%20the%20world%20and%20you%20cannot%20necessarily%20develop%20a%20general%20concept%20for%20each%20of%20them%20but%20you%20can%20work%20together%20on%20the%20essentials%20of%20peace%20and%20progress.%20Then%20I%20would%20say%20no%20two%20countries%20now%20are%20better%20situated%20to%20evolve%20their%20friendship%2C%26quot%3B%20Kissinger%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20day%20after%20Dhaka%20was%20liberated%20on%20December%2016%2C%201971%2C%20then%20President%20Nixon%20was%20told%20by%20Kissinger%20that%20he%20had%20%26quot%3Bsaved%20West%20Pakistan%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20confidential%20papers%20since%20declassified%20by%20the%20US%20State%20Department.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKissinger%20told%20then-President%20Gerald%20Ford%20after%20his%20meeting%20with%20Indira%20Gandhi%20in%20October%201974%2C%20a%20few%20months%20after%20India's%20first%20nuclear%20test%2C%20that%20she%20had%20felt%20an%20%26quot%3Balmost%20pathological%20need%26quot%3B%20to%20criticise%20the%20US%20but%20at%20the%20same%20time%20desired%20an%20improvement%20in%20Indo-US%20relations%20on%20a%20%26quot%3Bmore%20equal%26quot%3B%20basis%20after%20Washington%20recognised%20India%20as%20an%20%26quot%3Bimportant%20country%20in%20the%20world%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20once%20acknowledged%20that%20the%20then%20United%20States%20Republican%20administration%20had%20always%20wished%20it%20had%20a%20man%20as%20'strong'%20as%20Gandhi%2C%20but%20in%20the%20same%20breath%2C%20Kissinger%20said%20Gandhi%20did%20not%20have%20a%20personality%20that%20appealed%20at%20'first%20blush'%20to%20Americans.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20a%20visit%20to%20Afghanistan%20and%20in%20a%20meeting%20with%20Mohammad%20Daoud%2C%20the%20Head%20of%20State%20and%20Prime%20Minister%2C%20Kissinger%20shared%20a%20number%20of%20views%20including%20those%20on%20India%2C%20non-alignment%20and%20the%20personality%20of%20Gandhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20correct%20to%20say%20Mrs.%20Gandhi%20does%20not%20have%20a%20personality%20that%20appeals%20at%20first%20blush%20to%20Americans.%20Maybe%20not%20even%20at%20a%20second%20blush.%20There%20have%20even%20been%20cases%20of%20people%20who%20have%20resisted%20her%20a%20third%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Kissinger%20added%20when%20asked%20by%20Daoud%20to%20characterise%20relations%20between%20India%20and%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20relations%20with%20India%20are%20friendly%20and%20aloof.%20It's%20a%20fortunate%20thing%20the%20Indians%20are%20pacifists%2C%20otherwise%2C%20their%20neighbours%20would%20be%20worried.%20The%20first%20time%20we%20were%20in%20India%2C%20they%20told%20me%20that%20Kabul%20belonged%20to%20India%20too%2C%26quot%3B%20Kissinger%20has%20been%20recorded%20as%20having%20said%20according%20to%20a%20White%20House%20Memo.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKissinger%20received%20a%20Nobel%20Peace%20Prize%20in%201973%20for%20helping%20arrange%20the%20end%20of%20US%20military%20involvement%20in%20the%20disastrous%20Vietnam%20War.%20He%20is%20also%20credited%20with%20secret%20diplomacy%20that%20helped%20President%20Nixon%20open%20communist%20Ch