ngagement%22%3A102%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67565509%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67565509.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworld-europe-67565509.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Why%20India's%20Reactions%20To%20Canada%20And%20US%20On%20Khalistan%20Row%20Are%20Different%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Attorney%20for%20New%20York%20has%20charged%20Indian%20national%20Nikhil%20Gupta%20with%20murder-for-hire%20charges%20in%20the%20alleged%20foiled%20bid%20to%20kill%20Khalistani%20separatist%20Gurwatpant%20Pannun%20in%20the%20US.%20What%20is%20most%20significant%20is%20that%20the%20investigations%20by%20the%20US%20clearly%20state%20that%20Gupta%20was%20acting%20at%20the%20behest%20of%20an%20%26quot%3BIndian%20government%20employee%26quot%3B%2C%20drawing%20a%20connection%2C%20much%20like%20the%20Canadian%20government%20did%2C%20with%20what%20PM%20Justin%20Trudeau%20called%20%26quot%3Bagents%20of%20the%20Indian%20government%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20press%20release%20is%20far%20more%20damaging%20than%20any%20accusation%20by%20Canada.%20First%2C%20it%20mentions%20the%20antecedents%20of%20Nikhil%20Gupta%2C%20who%20was%20allegedly%20working%20with%20the%20%26quot%3BIndian%20government%20employee%26quot%3B%2C%20as%20being%20involved%20in%20serious%20crimes%20like%20%26quot%3Binternational%20narcotics%20and%20weapons%20trafficking%26quot%3B.%20Secondly%2C%20it%20lays%20bare%20the%20entire%20process%20by%20which%20the%20bid%20to%20kill%20Pannun%20was%20thwarted%2C%20which%20included%20US%20undercover%20officers%20getting%20direct%20information%20from%20Gupta%20on%20the%20instructions%20he%20was%20getting%20from%20the%20%26quot%3BIndian%20government%20employee%26quot%3B.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20official%20press%20release%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BOn%20or%20about%20June%2020%2C%202023%2C%20CC-1%20sent%20GUPTA%20a%20news%20article%20about%20the%20Victim%20and%20messaged%20GUPTA%2C%20%26quot%3B%5Bi%5Dt's%20%5Ba%5D%20priority%20now.%26quot%3B%20Where%20CC%20-%201%20refers%20to%20the%20%26quot%3BIndian%20government%20employee%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20undercover%20operation%20also%20points%20to%20the%20connection%20they%20made%20with%20Hardeep%20Singh%20Nijjar's%20killing%20in%20Canada.%20The%20press%20statement%20mentions%20that%20just%20two%20days%20before%20the%20message%20that%20Gupta%20received%20from%20CC-1%20to%20carry%20out%20the%20killing%20of%20Pannun%20on%20%26quot%3Bpriority%26quot%3B%2C%20Nijjar%20was%20killed%20in%20British%20Columbia%2C%20on%20June%2018.%20%26quot%3BOn%20or%20about%20June%2019%2C%202023%2C%20the%20day%20after%20the%20Nijjar%20murder%2C%20GUPTA%20told%20the%20UC%20that%20Nijjar%20'was%20also%20the%20target'%20and%20'we%20have%20so%20many%20targets'%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20opposed%20to%20this%2C%20so%20far%2C%20the%20Canadian%20government%20has%20not%20revealed%20any%20details%20of%20its%20investigation.%20On%20September%2018%20Justin%20Trudeau%20made%20a%20bombshell%20of%20an%20allegation%20against%20India%20in%20the%20Canadian%20parliament%20and%20then%20Foreign%20Minister%20Melanie%20Joly%20announced%20the%20expulsion%20of%20an%20Indian%20diplomat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20manner%20of%20the%20revelation%20was%20most%20probably%20the%20reason%20for%20India's%20sharp%20reaction.%20There%20were%20two%20issues%20here%20-%20one%2C%20that%20Justin%20Trudeau%20made%20the%20statement%20in%20parliament%20as%20investigations%20were%20underway%20and%20decided%20to%20move%20away%20from%20quiet%20diplomacy%20on%20the%20matter.%20Next%2C%20Melanie%20Joly's%20office%20identified%20the%20expelled%20Indian%20official%20to%20the%20Canadian%20media%20and%20added%20that%20he%20led%20the%20Canadian%20branch%20of%20the%20Research%20and%20Analysis%20Wing%20(RAW).%20This%2C%20while%20the%20officer%20was%20listed%20as%20a%20minister%20for%20economic%2C%20coordination%2C%20and%20community%20affairs%20on%20the%20Indian%20High%20Commission's%20website.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20fact%20that%20India%20has%2C%20even%20in%20the%20past%2C%20expressed%20its%20concern%20to%20Canada%20over%20its%20approach%20of%20dealing%20with%20Khalistan%20separatists%20with%20kid%20gloves%20and%20allowing%20its%20territory%20to%20be%20used%20for%20a%20referendum%20over%20a%20secessionist%20call%2C%20had%20already%20created%20a%20backdrop%20for%20larger%20friction%20after%20Trudeau's%20statement.%20So%2C%20India%20reacted%20with%20visa%20restrictions%20and%20a%20threat%20to%20revoke%20the%20diplomatic%20immunity%20of%20diplomats%2C%20resulting%20in%2041%20of%20them%20returning%20to%20Canada%20last%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhy%20hasn't%20New%20Delhi%20used%20a%20similar%20forceful%20approach%20against%20the%20US%3F%20Many%20put%20it%20flippantly%20as%2C%20Canada%20is%20no%20US.%20The%20other%2C%20more%20plausible%2C%20reason%20seems%20to%20be%20that%20while%20the%20US%20has%20conducted%20an%20investigation%20and%20revealed%20details%20and%20charges%2C%20Trudeau%20seemed%20to%20have%20jumped%20the%20gun%20because%20of%20domestic%20political%20requirements.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20many%20argue%20that%20details%20that%20have%20consistently%20been%20trickling%20in%20the%20US%20media%20-%20from%20the%20foiled%20bid%20on%20Pannun%20to%20the%20killing%20of%20Nijjar%20-%C2%A0%20and%20that%20they%20have%20cropped%20up%20in%20meetings%20between%20Indian%20officials%20and%20their%20American%20counterparts%2C%20which%20is%20as%20damaging%20as%20was%20Trudeau's%20parliament%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20formal%20announcement%20of%20charges%20by%20the%20US%2C%20the%20swirl%20of%20stories%20in%20the%20international%20media%2C%20and%20the%20point%20that%20the%20tip-off%20to%20Canada%20on%20the%20Nijjar%20killing%20was%20from%20the%20Five%20