20Kissinger%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5b43990442e1cc24f17e6bf5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222070%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDr.%20Henry%20Kissinger%2C%20professor%20at%20Harvard%20University%2C%20is%20seen%20Dec.%201968.%3Cp%3EAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EHenry%20Kissinger%20died%20at%20his%20Connecticut%20home.%20He%20was%20100.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20controversial%20and%20polarizing%20statesman%20made%20choices%20in%20foreign%20policy%20that%20impact%20the%20US%20today.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20started%20his%20life%20in%20Nazi%20Germany%20before%20his%20family%20fled%20to%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EDr.%20Henry%20Kissinger%2C%20scholar%20and%20former%20US%20secretary%20of%20state%2C%20died%20at%20100%20at%20his%20home%20in%20Connecticut%2C%20Kissinger%20Associates%2C%20Inc.%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%20did%20not%20provide%20a%20cause%20of%20death.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKissinger%20was%20born%20in%20Germany%20in%201923%2C%20and%20his%20family%20fled%20the%20Nazi%20regime%20to%20America%20in%201938.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20time%20as%20a%20US%20Secretary%20of%20State%2C%20he%20dramatically%20shifted%20US%20relations%20in%20the%20Cold%20War%2C%20in%20Vietnam%2C%20and%20in%20China%2C%20though%20his%20foreign%20policy%20approaches%20were%20just%20as%20heavily%20critiqued%20as%20they%20were%20lauded.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20%3Cspan%3Edominated%20foreign%20policy%20as%20the%20United%20States%20extricated%20itself%20from%20Vietnam%20and%20broke%20down%20barriers%20with%20China.%20Kissinger%20after%20he%20left%20government%20was%20dogged%20by%20critics%20who%20argued%20that%20he%20should%20be%20called%20to%20account%20for%20his%20policies%20on%20Southeast%20Asia%20and%20support%20of%20repressive%20regimes%20in%20Latin%20America.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201973%2C%20he%20received%20the%20Nobel%20Peace%20Prize%20for%20helping%20to%20broker%20the%20Paris%20Peace%20Accords%2C%20under%20which%20the%20US%20military%20agreed%20to%20withdraw%20from%20South%20Vietnam.%20But%20fighting%20went%20on%20for%20another%20two%20years%2C%20to%20devastating%20effect.%20In%201975%2C%20a%20day%20after%20the%20fall%20of%20Saigon%2C%20Kissinger%20attempted%20to%20return%20his%20prize%2C%20saying%20%3Cspan%3Ethe%20%26quot%3Bpeace%20we%20sought%20through%20negotiations%20has%20been%20overturned%20by%20force%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20recently-released%20nomination%20papers%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fnobel-prize-body-knew-kissingers-1973-vietnam-deal-unlikely-bring-peace-2023-01-11%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereported%20on%20by%20Reuters.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3EThe%20committee%20declined%20to%20take%20back%20the%20prize.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20is%20survived%20by%20his%20wife%20Nancy%20Kissinger%2C%20his%20two%20children%2C%20David%20and%20Elizabeth%2C%20and%20five%20grandchildren.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHe%20rose%20to%20prominence%20in%20politics%20while%20teaching%20at%20Harvard.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221900%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Richard%20Nixon%20Henry%20Kissinger%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5a663f80a244446b008b5101%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221261%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EJohn%20Duricka%2FAP%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20studying%20political%20history%20and%20getting%20a%20Ph.D.%20in%20government%20studies%2C%20he%20began%20working%20for%20Harvard's%20government%20department%20in%20the%20mid-1950s.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20still%20teaching%20there%2C%20Kissinger%20worked%20advising%20then-presidents%20John%20F.%20Kennedy%20and%20Lyndon%20B.%20Johnson%20on%20foreign%20policy%20decisions%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.fox5ny.com%2Fnews%2Fformer-secretary-of-state-henry-kissinger-dead-at-100%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%20Fox5%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHe%20was%20national%20security%20advisor%20from%201969%20to%201975.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20black%20and%20white%20photo%20of%20American%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Henry%20Kissinger%20(Right)%20standing%20next%20to%20Israeli%20Prime%20Minister%20Golda%20Meir%20(Left%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6524512868f1d46f52ac3109%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224256%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAmerican%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Henry%20Kissinger%20(Right)%20stands%20next%20to%20Israeli%20Prime%20Minister%20Golda%20Meir%20(Left)%3Cp%3E-%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20catching%20Nixon's%20attention%2C%20he%20was%20appointed%20security%20advisor%2C%20and%20subsequently%20nominated%20for%20the%20secretary%20of%20state%20position%20in%201973%2C%20per%20Fox5.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20time%2C%20he%20served%20in%20both%20roles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHe%20served%20as%20secretary%20of%20state%20from%201973%20to%201977.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222932%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22NEW%20YORK%2C%20NY%20-%20CIRCA%201990%3A%20Henry%20Kissinger%20circa%201976%20in%20New%20York%20City.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5faac67d1df1d50018219e0b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222223%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHenry%20Kissinger%20circa%201976%20in%20New%20York%20City.%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%20%2F%20Photo%20by%20PL%20Gould%2FImages%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20eight%20restless%20years%20%E2%80%94%20first%20as%20national%20security%20adviser%2C%20later%20as%20secretary%20of%20state%2C%20and%20for%20a%20time%20in%20the%20middle%20holding%20both%20titles%20%E2%80%94%20Kissinger%20ranged%20across%20the%20breadth%20of%20major%20foreign%20policy%20issues.%20He%20conducted%20the%20first%20%26quot%3Bshuttle%20diplomacy%26quot%3B%20in%20the%20quest%20for%20Middle%20East%20peace.%20He%20used%20secret%20channels%20to%20pursue%20ties%20between%20the%20United%20States%20and%20China%2C%20ending%20decades%20of%20isolation%20and%20mutual%20hostility.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20initiated%20the%20Paris%20negotiations%20that%20ultimately%20provided%20a%20face-saving%20means%20%E2%80%94%20a%20%26quot%3Bdecent%20interval%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20called%20it%20%E2%80%94%20to%20get%20the%20United%20States%20out%20of%20a%20costly%20war%20in%20Vietnam.%20Two%20years%20later%2C%20Saigon%20fell%20to%20the%20communists.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnd%20he%20pursued%20a%20policy%20of%20detente%20with%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20that%20led%20to%20arms%20control%20agreements%20and%20raised%20the%20possibility%20that%20the%20tensions%20of%20the%20Cold%20War%20and%20its%20nuclear%20threat%20did%20not%20have%20to%20last%20forever.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHe%20has%20also%20been%20harshly%20criticized%20and%20called%20a%20%26quot%3Bwar%20criminal%26quot%3B%20for%20his%20actions.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224256%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Xi%20Jinping%20and%20Henry%20Kissinger%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5841f2a7e02ba71b008b7560%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222837%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EXi%20Jinping%20and%20Henry%20Kissinger%3Cp%3ENicolas%20Asouri%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EKissinger%20was%20a%20practitioner%20of%20realpolitik%20%E2%80%94%20using%20diplomacy%20to%20achieve%20practical%20objectives%20rather%20than%20advance%20lofty%20ideals.%20Supporters%20said%20his%20pragmatic%20bent%20served%20U.S.%20interests%3B%20critics%20saw%20a%20Machiavellian%20approach%20that%20ran%20counter%20to%20democratic%20ideals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%202015%2C%20an%20appearance%20by%20the%2091-year-old%20Kissinger%20before%20the%20Senate%20Armed%20Services%20Committee%20was%20disrupted%20by%20protesters%20demanding%20his%20arrest%20for%20war%20crimes%20and%20calling%20out%20his%20actions%20in%20Southeast%20Asia%2C%20Chile%2C%20and%20beyond.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20a%202012%20Harvard%20appearance%2C%20Kissinger%20was%20confronted%20by%20one%20audience%20member%20about%20the%20deaths%20that%20resulted%20in%20his%20foreign%20policy%20maneuvering.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHow%20do%20you%20justify%20receiving%20the%20Nobel%20Peace%20Prize%20when%20you%20were%20the%20architect%20of%2C%20with%20Richard%20Nixon%2C%20of%20killing%20four%20million%20southeast%20Asians%20during%20the%20Vietnam%20War%3F%26quot%3B%20one%20audience%20member%20asked%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2023%2F11%2F29%2F915981256%2Fhenry-kissinger-dead%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eper%20NPR%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%26quot%3BDo%20you%20deny%20these%20war%20crimes%3F%20Basically%2C%20how%20do%20you%20sleep%20with%20yourself%20at%20night%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BJust%20study%20who%20did%20what%2C%20not%20people%20who%20live%20off%20proving%20their%20country%20is%20evil%20and%20their%20leaders%20are%20criminal%2C%26quot%3B%20Kissinger%20responded%2C%20according%20to%20NPR.%20%26quot%3BStart%20from%20the%20assumption%20that%20rational%20people%20were%20in%20government.%20What%20led%20to%20what%20decisions%3F%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20castigated%20for%20authorizing%20telephone%20wiretaps%20of%20reporters%20and%20his%20own%20National%20Security%20Council%20staff%20to%20plug%20news%20leaks%20in%20Nixon's%20White%20House.%20He%20was%20denounced%20on%20college%20campuses%20for%20the%20bombing%20and%20allied%20invasion%20of%20Cambodia%20in%20April%201970%2C%20intended%20to%20destroy%20North%20Vietnamese%20supply%20lines%20to%20communist%20forces%20in%20South%20Vietnam.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20%26quot%3Bincursion%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20Nixon%20and%20Kissinger%20called%20it%2C%20was%20blamed%20by%20some%20for%20contributing%20to%20Cambodia's%20fall%20into%20the%20hands%20of%20Khmer%20Rouge%20insurgents%20who%20later%20slaughtered%20some%202%20million%20Cambodians.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EIn%20his%20later%20years%2C%20he%20continued%20doing%20business%20trips%20and%20book%20deals.%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Former%20US%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Henry%20Kissinger%20speaking%20in%20October%202023%2C%20in%20an%20interview%20about%20the%20Gaza%20attack%20on%20Israel.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6527e6ea6561dd877e78b165%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22640%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFormer%20US%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Henry%20Kissinger%20speaking%20in%20October%202023%2C%20in%20an%20interview%20about%20the%20Gaza%20attack%20on%20Israel.%3Cp%3EAxel%20Springer%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20when%20he%20was%2099%2C%20Kissinger%20was%20still%20touring%20for%20his%20book%20about%20leadership.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EABC%20asked%20him%20in%20July%20of%20that%20year%20if%20he%20wished%20he%20could%20change%20any%20decisions%20he%20made%20previously%2C%20per%20AP.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20been%20thinking%20about%20these%20problems%20all%20my%20life.%20It's%20my%20hobby%20as%20well%20as%20my%20occupation%2C%26quot%3B%20Kissinger%20told%20ABC.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20the%20recommendations%20I%20made%20were%20the%20best%20of%20which%20I%20was%20then%20capable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20similarly%20dismissed%20claims%20of%20war%20crimes%20in%20a%20CBS%20interview%20shortly%20before%20his%20100th%20birthday%2C%20according%20to%20AP.%20During%20the%20interview%2C%20he%20was%20asked%20about%20people%20who%20think%20his%20conduct%20was%20akin%20to%20criminal%20behavior%20or%20reprehensible.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat's%20a%20reflection%20of%20their%20ignorance%2C%26quot%3B%20Kissinger%20said%20to%20CBS.%20%26quot%3BIt%20wasn't%20conceived%20that%20way.%20It%20wasn't%20conducted%20that%20way.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20ori