fication%2C%20sources%20told%20ABC.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20end%20of%20the%20meeting%2C%20Trump%20apparently%20agreed%20Corcoran%20would%20return%20to%20the%20Florida%20resort%20to%20search%20for%20any%20remaining%20classified%20records%20in%20the%20following%20days%2C%20the%20outlet%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20before%20Corcoran%20returned%20to%20search%20a%20basement%20storage%20room%2C%20Trump%20directed%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fread-superseding-indictment-against-trump-mar-a-lago-documents-case-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etwo%20co-defendants%20in%20the%20case%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20staffers%20Walt%20Nauta%20and%20Carlos%20De%20Oliveira%20to%20remove%20several%20boxes%20from%20the%20storage%20room%2C%20Smith%20alleged%20in%20the%20indictment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECorcoran%20later%20handed%20over%2038%20classified%20documents%20found%20in%20his%20basement%20search%20to%20the%20FBI%20along%20with%20a%20certification%20that%20Trump%20and%20his%20team%20had%20complied%20with%20the%20subpoena.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThree%20months%20later%2C%20however%2C%20FBI%20agents%20searched%20Mar-a-Lago%20and%20uncovered%20102%20additional%20documents%20marked%20classified.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-knew-crime-lie-classified-documentss-case-attorney-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701313059000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6547102736d588dc55cb079b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-knew-crime-lie-classified-documentss-case-attorney-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20lawyer%20for%20Trump%20told%20prosecutors%20she%20warned%20him%20he%20could%20face%20charges%20by%20failing%20to%20comply%20with%20a%20subpoena%20in%20the%20documents%20case%2C%20ABC%20News%20reported.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22esnodgrass%40insider.com%20(Er