3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fisrael-hamas-war-uk-sending-one-of-its-most-lethal-warships-to-gulf-to-deter-iran-backed-groups-13018926%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fisrael-hamas-war-uk-sending-one-of-its-most-lethal-warships-to-gulf-to-deter-iran-backed-groups-13018926%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bhutan%20National%20Elections%3A%20Voters%20Go%20to%20Polls%20With%20More%20Choice%20and%20Economy%20on%20Their%20Minds%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F29191235%2Fpexels-aboodi-vesakaran-13992201.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Bhutan%20will%20go%20to%20elections%20on%20Thursday%20for%20the%20fourth%20time%20after%20the%20erstwhile%20Himalayan%20kingdom%20transitioned%20to%20democracy%2C%20featuring%20the%20largest-ever%20field%20of%20five%20political%20parties%2C%20with%20economic%20issues%20taking%20centre%20stage.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBhutan%20is%20the%20youngest%20democracy%20in%20South%20Asia%2C%20having%20transitioned%20from%20a%20monarchy%20to%20a%20parliamentary%20system%20in%202008.%20It%20has%20gone%20through%20three%20general%20elections%2C%20each%20of%20them%20having%20seen%20the%20incumbent%20defeated%20and%20a%20new%20party%20given%20the%20chance%20to%20helm%20the%20government.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20November%2030%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ecb.bt%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2FNotification-for-Final-Electoral-Roll-Postal-Voter-List.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E496%2C836%20voters%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20are%20eligible%20to%20cast%20their%20votes%20to%20elect%20their%20candidates%20to%20the%2047%20seats%20of%20the%20fourth%20parliament.%20The%20number%20of%20registered%20voters%20has%20increased%20by%20around%2056%25%20since%20the%20first%20parliamentary%20elections%2C%20fifteen%20years%20ago.%20The%20voters%20would%20be%20going%20to%20the%20polls%20after%20a%20black-out%20period%20of%2048%20hours%20following%20the%20end%20of%20campaigning.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.nationalcouncil.bt%2Fassets%2Fuploads%2Fdocs%2Facts%2F2017%2FConstitution_of_Bhutan_2008.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EBhutan%E2%80%99s%20constitution%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20proscribes%20a%20two-tier%20system%20of%20National%20Assembly%20election.%20While%20all%20registered%20parties%20can%20take%20part%20in%20the%20primary%20round%20on%20Thursday%2C%20the%20two%20parties%20with%20the%20highest%20number%20of%20votes%20will%20go%20to%20the%20final%20run-off%20on%20January%209.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWho%20are%20the%20main%20parties%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFrom%20just%20two%20political%20parties%20in%202008%2C%20the%20number%20of%20political%20parties%20in%20this%20election%20has%20increased%20to%20five.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20two%20oldest%20are%20Druk%20Phuensum%20Tshogpa%20(DPT)%20and%20the%20People%E2%80%99s%20Democratic%20Party%20(PDP)%2C%20which%20won%20the%20first%20and%20second%20parliamentary%20elections%20respectively.%20The%20current%20ruling%20party%20is%20the%20Druk%20Nyamrup%20Tshogpa%20(DNT)%2C%20which%20caused%20an%20upset%20in%202018%20by%20ensuring%20that%20the%20then-incumbent%20PDP%20did%20not%20even%20go%20into%20the%20final%20round%20of%20the%202018%20elections.%20It%20won%2030%20out%20of%20the%2047%20seats.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20two%20youngest%20are%20the%20Druk%20Thuendrel%20Tshogpa%20(DTT)%20and%20the%20Bhutan%20Tendrel%20Party%20(BTP)%2C%20both%20of%20which%20have%20had%20to%20conduct%20innovative%20campaigns%20and%20branding%20to%20capture%20eyeballs.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWhat%20are%20the%20main%20issues%20in%20this%20election%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Bhutanese%20elections%20have%20had%20a%20distinctly%20calmer%20flavour%20which%20is%20unlike%20the%20frenzied%20electoral%20atmosphere%20of%20other%20South%20Asian%20polls.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBefore%20the%20end%20of%20the%20official%20campaign%20period%2C%20the%20Office%20of%20the%20Media%20Arbitrator%20(OMA)%20had%20claimed%20that%20it%20had%20only%20identified%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkuenselonline.com%2Flimited-hostility-among-political-parties%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E13%20posts%20of%20political%20parties%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20potentially%20discredited%20their%20rivals%2C%20which%20was%20a%20decrease%20compared%20to%20previous%20elections.%20However%2C%20a%20day%20before%20polls%2C%20four%20political%20parties%20complained%20to%20the%20OMA%20that%20the%20PDP%20president%2C%20former%20prime%20minister%20Tshering%20Tobgay%20had%20circulated%20a%20video%20claiming%20that%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkuenselonline.com%2Fparties-accuse-pdp-of-claiming-royal-patronage%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EBhutanese%20king%20wanted%20his%20party%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20return%20to%20power.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20an%20outsider%2C%20there%20is%20not%20much%20difference%20ideologically%20between%20the%20political%20parties.%20But%2C%20from%20the%20manifestos%20and%20the%20televised%20party%20debates%2C%20it%20was%20clear%20that%20the%20economy%20was%20at%20the%20top%20of%20the%20agenda.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CAll%20parties%20highlighted%20reviving%20%3Cem%3Epeljore%3C%2Fem%3E%20(economy)%2C%20pronounced%20as%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EPanjo%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20making%20it%20the%20most%20talked%20about%20during%20the%20campaign%20period%2C%20including%20providing%20content%20for%20social%20media%20memes%2C%E2%80%9D%20noted%20the%20Bhutanese%20paper%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkuenselonline.com%2Fas-we-head-to-the-polls%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EKuensel%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20editoria%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3El%20on%20Tuesday.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F10%2F19094212%2FScreen-Shot-2018-10-19-at-9.41.50-AM.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22945%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F10%2F19094212%2FScreen-Shot-2018-10-19-at-9.41.50-AM.png%20945w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F10%2F19094212%2FScreen-Shot-2018-10-19-at-9.41.50-AM-300x200.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-302520%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22632%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIncumbent%20Bhutan%20Prime%20Minister%20Lotay%20Tshering.%20Photo%3A%20Facebook%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWhat%20is%20the%20state%20of%20the%20economy%20as%20Bhutan%20goes%20to%20the%20polls%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELess%20than%20two%20years%20into%20the%20DNT%20government%2C%20the%20world%20went%20into%20lockdown.%20Bhutan%20had%20some%20of%20the%20strictest%20COVID-19%20restrictions%2C%20completely%20shutting%20down%20its%20borders%20to%20foreigners.%20It%20also%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Fthe-great-reboot%2Fbhutan-welcomes-back-tourists-after-covid-19-with-honey-turmeric-sim-cards-2022-09-23%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eloosened%20entry%20restrictions%20rather%20late%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20compared%20to%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%2C%20opening%20its%20tourist%20industry%20after%20a%20hiatus%20of%20more%20than%20two%20years%20in%20September%202022.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20the%20opening%20of%20borders%2C%20Bhutan%20did%20not%20reap%20the%20anticipated%20benefits%20due%20to%20a%20substantial%20increase%20in%20the%20tourism%20levy%20at%20the%20same%20time.%20The%20levy%20has%20been%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businesstraveller.com%2Fbusiness-travel%2F2023%2F09%2F02%2Fbhutan-cuts-sustainable-development-fee-by-50-per-cent%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DBhutan%2520has%2520slashed%2520its%2520Sustainable%2Ceffect%2520until%252031%2520August%252C%25202027.%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Epartially%20relaxed%20recently%20this%20year%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fopenknowledge.worldbank.org%2Fserver%2Fapi%2Fcore%2Fbitstreams%2F9ffd589a-dfb0-4942-b94a-b89c41fb93b6%2Fcontent%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20World%20Bank%20estimated%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20Bhutan%E2%80%99s%20economy%20would%20grow%20by%204%25%20this%20year%2C%20which%20is%20lower%20than%20the%204.6%25%20logged%20in%202022-23.%20However%2C%20this%20estimate%20is%20still%20higher%20than%20the%20previous%20forecast%20of%203.1%25%20for%20the%20current%20financial%20year.%20The%20reason%20given%20for%20the%20upward%20revision%20is%20%E2%80%9Cin%20part%20due%20to%20a%20major%20salary%20increase%20for%20government%20workers%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20WB%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOverall%2C%20Bhutan%20is%20anticipated%20to%20lag%20behind%20other%20small%20states%2C%20with%20private%20investment%20remaining%20subdued%2C%20credit%20supply%20constrained%20due%20to%20moratorium%20on%20new%20housing%20loans%20and%20high%20non-performing%20loans%20in%20the%20banking%20sector%2C%20according%20to%20the%20World%20Bank.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Bhutanese%20government%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bhutantoday.bt%2Fbhutans-civil-servants-set-for-major-salary-boost-as-sixth-pay-commission-report-revealed%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eannounced%20a%20hike%20of%2055-74%25%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20government%20salaries%20in%20June.%20This%20salary%20boost%20came%20against%20a%20backdrop%20of%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebhutanese.bt%2F16-percent-attrition-from-the-civil-service%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehigh%20rate%20of%20attrition%20among%20Bhutanese%20civil%20servants%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20which%20has%20seen%20a%20sharp%20increase%20in%20the%20past%20two%20years%2C%20with%20many%20migrating%20to%20foreign%20shores%20due%20to%20the%20rising%20cost%20of%20living.%20As%20per%20the%20Royal%20Civil%20Service%20Commission%20(RCSC)%2C%20the%20attrition%20rate%20in%202021-22%20was%204.65%25%2C%20which%20jumped%20to%2016%25%20in%202022-23.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20general%2C%20Bhutanese%20have%20migrated%20in%20large%20numbers%2C%20especially%20to%20Australia%2C%20with%20job%20generation%20scarce%20in%20non-hydropower%20sectors%20and%20youth%20unemployment%20recorded%20as%20high%20as%2029%25%20in%202022.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnother%20worrisome%20economic%20indicator%20is%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkuenselonline.com%2Fexternal-debt-servicing-rises%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eexternal%20debt%20service%20ratio%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20which%20has%20increased%20from%205.8%25%20in%202019-20%20to%2015.1%25%20in%202022-23.%20More%20than%20half%20of%20the%20debt%20servicing%20this%20year%20will%20be%20for%20the%20Mangdechhu%20power%20plant%20in%20Indian%20rupees.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20per%20the%20latest%20figures%20of%20Bhutan%E2%80%99s%20central%20bank%20Royal%20Monetary%20Authority%2C%20Bhutan%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rma.org.bt%2FRMA%2520Publication%2FMSB%2F2023%2FMonthly%2520Statistical%2520Bulletin%2520for%2520November%25202023.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eexternal%20reserves%20reached%20a%20low%20of%20%24467.05%20million%20in%20September%20this%20year%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20which%20is%20near%20the%20minimum%20threshold%20of%20%24464%20million%20determined%20by%20the%20government%20to%20meet%20the%20cost%20of%20one%20year%E2%80%99s%20worth%20of%20essential%20imports.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EWhat%20are%20the%20key%20indicators%20for%20Bhutan%20elections%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%202018%20National%20Assembly%20election%2C%20postal%20ballots%20had%20been%20decisive%20in%20bringing%20the%20DNT%20to%20power.%20Despite%20the%20ruling%20PDP%20securing%20more%20votes%20through%20electronic%20voting%20machines%20at%20polling%20booths%2C%20it%20came%20in%20third%20during%20the%20primary%20round%20and%20could%20not%20advance%20to%20the%20final%20run-off.%20The%20pivotal%20factor%20was%20the%20DNT%E2%80%99s%20advantage%20in%20postal%20ballots%2C%20typically%20cast%20by%20civil%20servants%2C%20employees%20of%20state%20enterprises%2C%20students%2C%20and%20others%20who%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20vote%20in%20their%20hometowns.%20More%20than%2036%25%20of%20the%20votes%20cast%20in%20the%20primary%20and%20final%20round%20of%20the%202018%20polls%20were%20through%20postal%20ballots.%20In%20a%20few%20constituencies%20during%20those%20elections%2C%20postal%20ballots%20surpassed%20electronic%20voting%20machine%20(EVM)%20votes.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20things%20are%20being%20done%20differently%20this%20time.%20Unlike%202018%2C%20there%20are%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbs.bt%2Fnews%2F%3Fp%3D193946%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eno%20facilitation%20booths%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20available%20to%20assist%20voters%20who%20may%20find%20the%20process%20complex%20in%20casting%20their%20postal%20ballots.%20Additionally%2C%20the%20previous%20practice%20of%20generously%20distributing%20postal%20ballots%20is%20now%20limited%20exclusively%20to%20categories%20specified%20in%20the%202018%20law%2C%20which%20are%20diplomats%20and%20officials%20posted%20abroad%2C%20armed%20forces%2C%20civil%20servants%20and%20students.%20It%20leaves%20out%20Bhutanese%20nationals%20residing%20in%20foreign%20countries%2C%20and%20employees%20in%20public%20enterprises%20and%20the%20private%20sector.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EConcerns%20have%20been%20raised%20about%20the%20potential%20impact%20of%20restrictions%20on%20postal%20ballots%20on%20voter%20turnout%20in%20this%20election%20compared%20to%20previous%20ones.%20The%20highest-ever%20voter%20turnout%20was%2079.4%25%20in%20the%202008%20election.%20It%20was%20followed%20by%2071.46%25%20in%20the%20final%20round%20of%20the%202018%20elections.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20has%20always%20been%20a%20strong%20regional%20polarisation%20in%20votes%20for%20parties.%20DPT%20was%20known%20for%20its%20strong%20base%20in%20western%20regions%2C%20while%20PDP%20and%20DNT%20had%20both%20scored%20well%20in%20the%20southern%20and%20eastern%20constituencies%20in%202018.%20In%20the%20last%20round%20of%20the%202018%20polls%2C%20PDP%E2%80%99s%20voters%20had%20supported%20the%20DNT%20over%20its%20rival%20DPT%2C%20which%20almost%20divided%20the%20kingdom%20between%20the%20two%20parties%20down%20the%20middle.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20the%20two%20more%20parties%20in%20the%20fray%2C%20there%20is%20going%20to%20be%20fragmentation%20of%20votes%2C%20which%20may%20lead%20to%20unpredictable%20results.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3EIs%20India%20a%20factor%20in%20the%20elections%20at%20all%3F%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20is%20Bhutan%E2%80%99s%20largest%20source%20for%20development%20assistance%20and%20also%20the%20largest%20trade%20partner.%20Bhutan%20shares%20borders%20with%20only%20two%20countries%2C%20but%20it%20has%20no%20official%20diplomatic%20relations%20with%20China.%20Therefore%2C%20India%20looms%20large%20in%20Bhutan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20often%20said%20that%20India%20had%20been%20a%20factor%20in%20the%202013%20elections%2C%20as%20the%20polls%20came%20just%20after%20New%20Delhi%20ended%20and%20then%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Findustry%2Fenergy%2Foil-gas%2Findia-to-restore-subsidised-gas-supply-to-bhutan-from-august-1%2Farticleshow%2F21487817.cms%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Erestored%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20the%20subsidy%20for%20cooking%20gas.%20It%20was%20perceived%20as%20a%20sign%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20unhappiness%20with%20the%20DPT%20government%2C%20which%20had%20made%20overtures%20towards%20China.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Doklam%20stand-off%20took%20place%20a%20year%20before%20the%202018%20elections%2C%20but%20it%20did%20not%20cast%20any%20shadow%20over%20the%20polls%20with%20voters%20focused%20on%20economic%20issues.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20last%20year%2C%20there%20has%20been%20an%20acceleration%20in%20the%20border%20talks%20between%20Bhutan%20and%20China%2C%20after%20both%20sides%20signed%20an%20agreement%20on%20a%20%E2%80%9Cthree-step%20roadmap%E2%80%9D%20to%20resolve%20the%20border.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20this%2C%20India%20has%20not%20shown%20public%20concern%20and%20has%20not%20taken%20any%20actions%20indicating%20dissatisfaction%20with%20Prime%20Minister%20Lotay%20Tshering%E2%80%99s%20efforts%20to%20resolve%20the%20border%20issue%20with%20China.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F24173057%2FThe-Wire-53.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F24173057%2FThe-Wire-53.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F24173057%2FThe-Wire-53-300x140.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F24173057%2FThe-Wire-53-1024x478.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-681555%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EChinese%20foreign%20minister%20Wang%20Yi%20Bhutan%E2%80%99s%20foreign%20minister%20Tandi%20Dorji%20in%20Beijing%20on%20October%2023%2C%202023.%20Photo%3A%20Ministry%20of%20Foreign%20Affairs%2C%20China%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIncidentally%2C%20among%20the%20parties%2C%20only%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22about%3Ablank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EDPT%E2%80%99s%20manifesto%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20has%20a%20specific%20reference%20to%20India%20in%20terms%20of%20foreign%20policy.%20%E2%80%9CThroughout%20all%20our%20foreign%20policy%20initiatives%2C%20our%20Party%20will%20prioritize%20strengthening%20our%20connections%20with%20the%20People%20and%20Government%20of%20India%20and%20maintaining%20friendly%20relations%20with%20our%20neighbouring%20nations%2C%E2%80%9D%20promised%20the%20party.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAll%20of%20them%20have%20proposals%20for%20increasing%20cooperation%20with%20India%20in%20the%20hydropower%20sector%20and%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ecb.bt%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2FPP_Manifesto%2FDNT-Manifesto-03112023.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Efacilitating%20trade%20ties%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20but%20with%20also%20an%20eye%20on%20diversification.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ecb.bt%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2FPP_Manifesto%2FDNT-Manifesto-03112023.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20ruling%20DNT%20party%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20noted%20that%20%E2%80%9Cour%20partnership%20with%20India%20will%20continue%20to%20be%20the%20cornerstone%20of%20our%20hydropower%20and%20energy%20sector%E2%80%9D.%20%E2%80%9CIn%20addition%2C%20the%20projects%20to%20build%20small%20hydropower%20projects%20on%20our%20own%20will%20be%20further%20expanded%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20