x768.jpeg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F29151251%2FBJP-300x225.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F29151251%2FBJP.jpeg%201200w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686919%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22630%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20removal%20of%20Bandi%20Sanjay%20Kumar%20(third%20from%20right)%20as%20state%20chief%20is%20seen%20by%20many%20as%20taking%20the%20edge%20off%20the%20saffron%20party%E2%80%99s%20campaign%20in%20Telangana.%20Photo%3A%20X%2F%40BJP4Telangana.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20unlike%20the%20BRS%20and%20Congress%2C%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20manifesto%20does%20not%20promise%20the%20same%20extent%20of%20financial%20assistance%20or%20%E2%80%98pension%E2%80%99%20schemes%2C%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Felections%2Ftelangana-assembly%2Fhome-minister-amit-shah-likely-to-release-bjp-manifesto-by-the-weekend%2Farticle67531643.ece%5C%22%3EAmit%20Shah%20said%20earlier%20this%20month%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20party%20had%20%E2%80%9Cclearly%20demarcated%20a%20%3Cem%3Elakshman%20rekha%3C%2Fem%3E%20with%20regard%20to%20welfare%20versus%20freebies%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20farmers%2C%20the%20saffron%20party%20promises%20(among%20other%20things)%20Rs%202%2C500%20as%20input%20assistance%20for%20seeds%20and%20fertilisers%20to%20small%20farmers%20in%20addition%20to%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20Modi%20government%E2%80%99s%20fertiliser%20subsidy%20of%20over%20Rs%2018%2C000%20per%20acre%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20promised%20health%20insurance%20worth%20Rs%2010%20lakh%20for%20eligible%20families%20under%20its%20Ayushman%20Bharat%20scheme%20and%20said%20it%20will%20leverage%20funds%20under%20the%20rural%20edition%20of%20the%20PM%20Awas%20Yojna%2C%20claiming%20the%20BRS%20has%20not%20used%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20caste%2C%20some%20of%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20promises%20include%20making%20a%20BC%20leader%20as%20chief%20minister%20if%20elected%20to%20power%20and%20increasing%20reservations%20for%20OBCs%2C%20SCs%20and%20STs%20by%20abolishing%20and%20reallocating%20the%20quota%20for%20Muslims%2C%20which%20it%20maintains%20is%20unconstitutional.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20the%20BRS%20and%20Congress%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20also%20made%20promises%20regarding%20LPG%20cylinders%2C%20but%20unlike%20them%2C%20it%20has%20promised%20instead%20to%20give%20four%20gas%20cylinders%20for%20free%20to%20beneficiaries%20of%20the%20PM%20Ujjwala%20scheme.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%20has%20also%20promised%20free%20laptops%20to%20undergraduate%20women%20students%20or%20women%20entering%20professional%20college%20courses%2C%20and%20a%20fixed%20deposit%20scheme%20that%20will%20allow%20newborn%20girls%20to%20receive%20Rs%201%20lakh%20when%20they%20turn%2018%20and%20another%20lakh%20when%20they%20turn%2021.%20It%20did%20not%20specify%20eligibility%20criteria%20in%20the%20manifesto%20text.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20some%20of%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20most%20salient%20promises%20are%20under%20its%20manifesto%E2%80%99s%20heritage%20and%20culture%20section.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%2C%20it%20says%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccurrent%20dispensation%E2%80%9D%20has%20%E2%80%98undermined%E2%80%99%20the%20efforts%20of%20those%20who%20died%20during%20Hyderabad%E2%80%99s%20accession%20to%20India%20by%20celebrating%20its%20anniversaries%20as%20Hyderabad%20Integration%20Day%20instead%20of%20%E2%80%9CHyderabad%20Liberation%20Day%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20it%20promises%20to%20celebrate%20instead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20promises%20to%20observe%20August%2027%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fhyderabad-razakar-owaisi-amit-shah-ktr%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CRazakars%20Horrors%20Remembrance%20Day%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20lines%20of%20%E2%80%9CPartition%20Horrors%20Remembrance%20Day%E2%80%9D%20as%20well%20as%20to%20encourage%20the%20%E2%80%9Crejuvenation%20of%20temples%20across%20the%20state%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20the%20party%20declared%20that%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccomplete%20ban%20on%20cow%20slaughter%20will%20be%20implemented%20in%20the%20state%20as%20per%20Article%2048%20of%20the%20constitution%E2%80%9D.%20Offenders%20under%20its%20proposed%20law%20will%20be%20punished%20with%20prison%20time%20between%20three%20and%20seven%20years%20and%2For%20with%20a%20fine%20between%20Rs%2050%2C000%20and%20Rs%205%20lakh%2C%20the%20BJP%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20any%20farmer%20wishing%20to%20possess%20a%20cow%20will%20be%20given%20a%20healthy%2C%20milk-yielding%20cow%20in%20tie-ups%20with%20%3Cem%3Egoshala%3C%2Fem%3Es.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701265244000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F29161723%2FFotoJet-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fcomparison-of-telangana-brs-congress-bjp-manifestos-2023%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20ruling%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samithi%20and%20the%20primary%20opposition%20Congress%20party%20have%20tried%20to%20outdo%20each%20other%20on%20welfare-related%20promises.%20Some%20of%20the%20BJP's%20most%20salient%20promises%20stem%20from%20its%20Hindutva%20ideology.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fcomparison-of-telangana-brs-congress-bjp-manifestos-2023%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22River%20Water%20Plays%20an%20Unspoken%20But%20Key%20Role%20in%20Telangana%20Elections%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F29145918%2F1024px-Nwgbridge.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESometime%20in%20the%2016th%20century%2C%20Muhammad%20Quli%20Qutb%20Shah%2C%20the%20founder%20of%20the%20city%20of%20Bhagnagar%20(present%20day%20Hyderabad)%2C%20prayed%3A%20%E2%80%9CMera%20shahar%20logaan%20se%20maamur%20kar%2C%20rakhyaa%20jun%20tun%20daryaa%20mein%20min%20yaa%20sami%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3E(%E2%80%9CFill%20my%20city%20with%20people%2C%20as%20you%20would%2C%20a%20river%20with%20fish%E2%80%9D).%C2%A0%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHis%20prayers%20were%20answered%20(for%20better%20or%20for%20worse).%20The%20metaphor%20of%20a%20river%20was%20significant%2C%20so%20also%20the%20fish%20(the%20metro%20city)%2C%20constantly%20needing%20water.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202009%2C%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newindianexpress.com%2Fopinions%2F2009%2Fdec%2F17%2Fpolitical-economy-regional-articulation-113590.html%5C%22%3Ewrote%3C%2Fa%3E%20an%20opinion%20article%20for%20the%3Cem%3E%20New%20Indian%20Express%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Etitled%20%E2%80%98River%20Water%20Holds%20the%20Key%E2%80%99%2C%20saying%20that%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20Godavari%20river%2C%20in%20no%20small%20way%2C%20will%20decide%20the%20future%20of%20a%20state%2C%20and%20if%20another%20is%20formed%2C%20the%20future%20of%20the%20river%20itself%E2%80%A6At%20stake%20are%20crores%20of%20rupees%20invested%20in%20irrigation%20projects%2C%20SEZs%2C%20hydel%20power%20projects%20and%20thereby%2C%20real%20estate%20activity%20in%20and%20around%20Hyderabad%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDid%20something%20change%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeventy-nine%20per%20cent%20of%20Godavari%20river%E2%80%99s%20and%2068%25%20of%20Krishna%20river%E2%80%99s%20catchment%20area%20lies%20in%20Telangana.%20Other%20important%20rivers%20in%20the%20region%20include%20Bhima%2C%20Dindi%2C%20Kinnerasani%2C%20Manjeera%2C%20Manair%2C%20Penganga%2C%20Pranahita%2C%20Peddavagu%20and%20Taliperu.%20The%20Pranahita%20river%20is%20a%20confluence%20of%20the%20Wainganga%20and%20Penganga%2C%20connecting%20it%20to%20Maharashtra.%20The%20drainage%20basin%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20now%20part%20of%20the%20political%20discourse%20%E2%80%93%20has%20an%20estimated%20annual%20discharge%20of%20280%20TMC%20(thousand%20million%20cubic%20feet)%2C%20coursing%20through%20forests%20and%20wildlife%20sanctuaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it%20is%20not%20the%20river%20or%20water%20per%20se%20but%20rather%20how%20it%20is%20imagined%20that%20determines%20the%20course%20of%20this%20region%E2%80%99s%20political%20and%20economic%20history.%20As%20to%20who%20imagines%20the%20river%2C%20or%20lives%20with%20her%2Fit%2C%20or%20is%20rendered%20broken%20on%20account%20of%20it%20all%2C%20it%20also%20makes%20a%20difference%20to%20the%20discourse.%20However%2C%20rarely%2C%20if%20ever%2C%20do%20you%20find%20them%20%E2%80%93%20the%20broken%20%E2%80%93%20at%20centre%20stage.%20A%20purely%20anthropocentric%20river%20discourse%2C%20and%20critiques%20along%20the%20same%20line%2C%20cannot%20suffice.%20It%20is%20desirable%20to%20be%20mindful%20of%20the%20ecology%20or%20environment%20in%20relation%20to%20the%20rivers%2C%20roadways%20and%20highways.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it%20is%20also%20possible%20perhaps%2C%20from%20stray%20(but%20freak)%20movements%20of%20the%20non-human%20actors%2Fpersons%2C%20who%20remind%20us%20of%20their%20vulnerability%20amidst%20the%20mightier%20river%20and%20roadways%E2%80%99%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fthis-tiger-becomes-indias-first-ever-to-have-walked-nearly-1700-km-6189094%2F%5C%22%3Eengineering%20ambitions%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20leaders%20of%20states%20assume%20the%20image%20of%20water%20providers%20within%20mainstream%20anthropocentric%20religious%20mythologies%20that%20imagine%20humans%20as%20lording%20over%20nature%2C%20paradoxically%20akin%20to%20the%20scientific%20modernity%20discourse%2C%20they%20ignore%20the%20larger%20mission%20of%20rivers%2C%20seasonality%2C%20or%20the%20natural%20rhythm%20regulating%20the%20ebbs%20and%20flows%20of%20river%20systems%20and%20aquatic%20life.%20In%20the%20present%20logic%20of%20continuous%20water%20supply%20through%20the%20year%20for%20cities%2C%20towns%2C%20and%20fields%2C%20a%20two-dimensional%20landscape%20with%20vertical%20housing%20structures%20and%20a%20different%20kind%20of%20universal%20history%20of%20cities%20is%20being%20imposed.%20And%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20spectrum%2C%20you%20have%20the%20%E2%80%98Smart%20City%E2%80%99%20concept%2C%20which%20necessitates%20continuous%20electricity%2C%20water%2C%20urban%20mobility%2C%20and%20seamless%20IT%20connectivity%20through%20optic%20fibre%20networks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20for%20Telangana%20and%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20from%20the%20arrival%20of%20rivers%20and%20their%20%E2%80%98stay%E2%80%99%20in%20the%20rightful%20season%20to%20backwater%20floods%20in%20Kaleshwaram%20and%20coffer-dam%20flooding%20in%20Polavaram%2C%20inundating%20newer%20spaces%20for%20longer%20periods%2C%20political%20floods%20are%20here%20to%20stay.%20Too%20much%20money%20has%20flowed%20under%20those%20canals%2C%20and%20roads%2C%20by%20now%2C%20and%20that%20money%20is%20also%20powering%20the%20course%20of%20our%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Frural-telangana-water-crisis%5C%22%3EIn%20Spite%20of%20Mega%20Projects%2C%20Water%20Is%20Scarce%20in%20Rural%20Telangana%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWater%2C%20ego%2C%20power%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECulturally%20speaking%2C%20though%20Telangana%20has%20come%20a%20long%20way%20in%20terms%20of%20reclaiming%20its%20sense%20of%20pride%20in%20terms%20of%20identity%2C%20be%20it%20in%20the%20celebrations%20of%20the%20local%20Ganga-Jamuni%20Hyderabadi%20%3Cem%3Etehzeeb%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20or%20festivals%20such%20as%20Bathukamma%20or%20Bonalu%20%E2%80%93%20the%20former%20is%20intrinsically%20linked%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3Echeruvus%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Elakes%2C%20tanks%2C%20and%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20centrality%20of%20the%20Telangana%20language%20%E2%80%93%20the%20power%20language%20%E2%80%93%20in%20Telugu%20mainstream%20cinema.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20Telangana%20movement%20expressed%20other%20hopes%20as%20well.%20Discussions%20had%20revolved%20around%20alternate%2C%20or%20smaller%2C%20technologies%20of%20river%20water%20utilisation%2C%20sustainable%20agriculture%2C%20biodiversity%20with%20regard%20to%20the%20big%20dam%20(Polavaram)%20ideas%2C%20which%20the%20then%20Andhra-based%20political%20leadership%20was%20supposed%20to%20be%20championing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPublic%20discourses%20regularly%20raised%20these%20perspectives.%20For%20instance%2C%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20gravity%20flow%20in%20%5Bunited%5D%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20the%20irrigated%20land%20is%20approximately%2069%20lakh%20acres%2C%20out%20of%20which%2060%20lakh%20acres%20are%20in%20the%20Andhra%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Telangana%2C%20what%20are%20the%20projects%20under%20gravity%20flow%2C%20barring%20the%20Sriram%20Sagar%20project%3F%20That%20too%2C%20under%20Phase%20I%2C%20which%20was%20meant%20to%20provide%20water%20for%209.68%20lakh%20acres%3B%20it%20is%20not%20feeding%20more%20than%204.5%20lakh%20acres%20under%20kharif%20for%20just%20a%20single%20crop.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Krishna%20river%20flows%20over%20the%20heart%20and%20body%20of%20Palamur%2C%20but%20does%20not%20reach%20the%20parched%20throats%20of%20the%20Palamur%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Krishna%20and%20Tungabhadra%20just%20remain%20rivers%3B%20what%20is%20left%20for%20Mahbubnagar%2C%20except%20tears%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20conspiracy%20to%20take%20Godavari%20waters%20to%20Krishna%20through%20%5BNagarjuna%5D%20Sagar%2C%20through%20Srisailam%20and%20Pothirreddypadu%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPeople%20had%20anticipated%20that%20the%20new%20state%20would%20implement%20smaller%20projects%20and%20address%20these%20disparities.%20Some%20of%20those%20discussions%20possibly%20led%20to%20the%20K.%20Chandrashekar%20Rao%20(KCR)%20government%E2%80%99s%20projects%2C%20such%20as%20Mission%20Kakatiya%2C%20Mission%20Bhagiratha%2C%20and%20Kaleshwaram%20Lift%20Irrigation%20Project%20(KLIP)%2C%20which%20was%20named%20as%20Pranahita-Chevella.%20However%2C%20opposition%20parties%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thenewsminute.com%2Fandhra-pradesh%2Fys-sharmila-files-complaint-cag-alleging-massive-corruption-kaleshwaram-project-169132%5C%22%3Ehave%20levelled%3C%2Fa%3E%20massive%20corruption%20allegations%20against%20KLIP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20the%20super-ambitious%20Kaleshwaram%20project%20is%20to%20the%20KCR%20regime%20what%20the%20super-ambitious%20Polavaram%20was%20to%20the%20Y.S.%20Rajasekhara%20Reddy%E2%80%99s%20regime%20of%20pre-Telangana.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20invocation%20of%20the%20Vedic-Sanskritic%20mythological%20sage%2C%20Bhagiratha%2C%20remains%20unchanged%20from%20the%20times%20of%20YSR%20(Jalayagam).%20The%20necessarily%20male%20figures%20who%20have%20ruled%20the%20states%20of%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20and%20Telangana%20have%20never%20tired%20of%20employing%20this%20metaphor%20of%20%E2%80%98bringing%20water%E2%80%99%20to%20the%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20KLIP%20manages%20to%20lift%20the%20Godavari%20water%20to%20a%20height%20of%20618%20metres%20from%20its%20source%20to%20the%20Kondapochamma%20Sagar%20reservoir%20in%20Gajwel%20district%2C%20227%20kilometres%20away.%20It%20comprises%20three%20barrages%2C%2019%20reservoirs%2C%2022%20pump%20houses%2C%20a%20204%20km%20underground%20tunnel%2C%20a%209%20km%20pumping%20main%2C%20seven%20links%2C%2028%20packages%2C%20through%2013%20districts%2C%20utilising%20a%20canal%20network%20of%20more%20than%201%2C800%20km%20to%20produce%20a%20total%20of%20240%20TMC%20water%2C%20of%20which%20169%20TMC%20is%20used%20for%20irrigation%2C%2030%20TMC%20for%20the%20Hyderabad%20urban%20municipal%20water%20supply%2C%2016%20TMC%20for%20miscellaneous%20industrial%20uses%2C%20and%20the%20remaining%20for%20evaporation%20loss.%20Out%20of%20the%20total%20240%20TMC%20of%20water%2C%20195%20TMC%20comes%20from%20Medigadda%20Barrage%2C%2020%20TMC%20from%20the%20Sripada%20Yellampalli%20project%2C%20and%2025%20TMC%20from%20groundwater.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20KLIP%20has%20four%20pumping%20facilities%20at%20Ramadugu%2C%20Medaram%2C%20Annaram%2C%20and%20Sundilla.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIncidentally%2C%2015%2C200%20acres%20of%20the%20ayacut%20and%20nine%20villages%20in%20Siddipet%20district%2C%20which%20is%20KCR%E2%80%99s%20constituency%20and%20where%20his%20sprawling%20farm%20is%20located%2C%20are%20expected%20to%20benefit%20from%20Package%2010%20of%20the%20Kaleshwaram%E2%80%99s%20Link%20IV.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20pillars%2019%2C%2020%2C%20and%2021%20of%20the%20Medigadda%20barrage%20have%20developed%20cracks%20with%20sinking%20sand%20beds%20due%20to%20heavy%20downpours%20in%20October%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EActivists%20emphasise%20that%20the%20governing%20authorities%20failed%20to%20conduct%20a%20comprehensive%20study%20of%20the%20vulnerable%20dynamics%20within%20the%20Godavari-Pranahita%20sub-basin%20and%20neglected%20dam%20safety%20analysis.%20Additionally%2C%20critics%20argue%20that%20the%20project%20is%20financially%20burdensome%2C%20with%20an%20estimated%20cost%20of%20Rs%2050%2C000%20per%20acre%20for%20cultivating%20paddy%20%E2%80%93%20an%20expense%20expected%20to%20be%20borne%20by%20future%20water%20consumers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20multiple%20projects%2C%20including%20dams%2C%20barrages%2C%20and%20lifts%20are%20planned%20along%20the%20Godavari%20river%20between%20Maharashtra%20and%20Telangana%2C%20a%20new%20question%20emerges%3A%20Will%20there%20be%20a%20sufficient%20volume%20of%20water%2C%20as%20initially%20projected%20for%20storage%20at%20the%20downstream%20Polavaram%20project%2C%20considering%20potential%20changes%20in%20climate%20regimes%20in%20the%20future%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20non-Anthropos%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20February%2024%2C%202018%2C%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fcities%2FHyderabad%2F22-25-lakh-trees-make-way-for-kaleshwaram-project%2Farticle22847413.ece%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20loss%20of%20forest%20cover%20to%20an%20extent%20of%20over%207%2C800%20acres%20on%20account%20of%20the%20KLIP.%3Cstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20daily%20reported%20that%20officially%2C%2022%20lakh%20forest%20trees%20were%20to%20be%20hacked%20for%20the%20same.%20The%20unofficial%20count%20could%20be%20more.%20Citing%20the%20Environmental%20Impact%20Assessment%20(EIA)%20conducted%20by%20the%20EPTRI%2C%20the%20report%20said%20that%20forest%20land%20in%20nine%20divisions%20of%20Mahadevpur%2C%20Sircilla%2C%20Siddipet%2C%20Yadadri%2C%20Medak%2C%20Nizamabad%2C%20Banswada%20and%20Nirmal%20came%20under%20the%20project.%20At%20least%20391%20plant%20species%2C%20six%20of%20which%20were%20in%20the%20IUCN%20(International%20Union%20for%20Conservation%20of%20Nature)%20vulnerable%20species%20list%2C%20would%20also%20be%20impacted%20due%20to%20the%20project%2C%20besides%20butterflies%20and%20moths%20(26)%2C%20dragonflies%2C%20birds%20(75)%2C%20reptiles%20(11)%2C%20amphibians%20(five)%2C%20mammals%20(16)%2C%20spiders%20(five).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20the%20NGT%2C%20too%2C%20had%20invalidated%20the%20environment%20clearance%20given%20to%20the%20Kaleshwaram%20project%2C%20based%20on%20a%20petition%20filed%20in%202018%2C%20saying%20that%20the%20Telangana%20(TRS)%20government%20had%20changed%20the%20project%20design%20by%20adding%20Mission%20Bhagiratha%20(drinking%20water%20supply%20from%20Krishna%20and%20Godavari%20to%20rural%20and%20urban%20Telangana)%20to%20it.%20However%2C%20as%20with%20the%20Polavaram%20dam%2C%20this%20too%2C%20passed%20muster.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20December%202019%2C%20a%20sub-adult%20male%20tiger%20named%20T1-C1%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Findia%2Fthis-tiger-becomes-indias-first-ever-to-have-walked-nearly-1700-km-6189094%2F%5C%22%3Eaged%20three%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Ftiger-s-1-500-km-night-walk-creates-record%2Fstory-xJi1ISLZjS9u5utgbXacoM.html%5C%22%3Ecovered%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Fscience%2Fstory%2Ftiger-travels-search-territory-mate-maharashtra-telangana-1624257-2019-12-01%5C%22%3Ea%20distance%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Fscience%2Fstory%2Ftiger-travels-search-territory-mate-maharashtra-telangana-1624257-2019-12-01%5C%22%3Eof%201%2C300%20km%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Tipeshwar%20Wildlife%20Sanctuary%20in%20Yavatmal.%20(Some%20reports%20suggest%20distances%20of%201%2C500%20or%20even%201%2C700%20km.)%20This%20journey%20spanned%20the%20political%20boundaries%20of%20Maharashtra%20and%20Telangana%2C%20traversing%20not%20only%20six%20(or%20possibly%20eight)%20administrative%20districts%20but%20also%20four%20designated%20wildlife%20sanctuaries%20in%20these%20states.%20The%20details%20were%20extensively%20covered%20in%20reports%20from%20TOI%2C%20ENS%2C%20and%20other%20reputable%20sources.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20traversed%20through%20Adilabad%20in%20Telangana%20and%20then%20to%20Painganga%20Sanctuary%2C%20leading%20few%20wildlife%20experts%20to%20raise%20concerns%20about%20deforestation%2C%20shrinking%20habitat%2C%20and%20scarcity%20of%20food.%20Over%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20tiger%20movements%20have%20often%20been%20reported%20along%20the%20Maharashtra-Telangana%20border%2C%20some%20leading%20to%20animal-human%20conflict%2C%20as%20well.%20Reports%20of%20tigers%20searching%20for%20a%20new%20territory%20need%20further%20probe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20a%20migration%20of%20a%20tiger%20from%20Thadoba%20Reserve%20in%20Maharashtra%20to%20Kagaznagar%20in%20Telangana%20was%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETigers%20are%20known%20to%20cross%20the%20Pranahita%20river%20and%20enter%20the%20Adilabad%20district%20after%20crossing%20the%20Penganga.%20Two%20years%20ago%2C%20conservationists%20also%20noted%20the%20movement%20of%20tigers%20from%20Maharashtra%20to%20Chennur%20and%20Mahadevpur%2C%20incidentally%2C%20closer%20to%20the%20Kaleshwaram%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20one%20of%20the%20public%20meetings%20at%20Warangal%20in%202010%2C%20a%20writer%20shared%20a%20page%20from%20history%2C%20which%20seemed%20poetic%3A%203%2C000%20years%20ago%2C%20the%20Buddha%20cleansed%20his%20feet%20in%20the%20Godavari%20river%20after%20crossing%20Adilabad%20near%20Kotilingalu.%20T1-C1%2C%20too%2C%20perhaps%2C%20was%20searching%20for%20this%20kind%20of%20peaceful%20metaphor%20in%20his%20(and%20by%20extension%2C%20our%20collective)%20survival%20story%2C%20outside%20of%20electoral%20gains.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701264616000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F29145918%2F1024px-Nwgbridge.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Friver-water-plays-an-unspoken-but-key-role-in-telangana-elections%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22It%20is%20not%20the%20river%20or%20water%20per%20se%20but%20rather%20how%20it%20is%20imagined%20that%20determines%20the%20course%20of%20this%20region's%20political%20and%20economic%20history.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Friver-water-plays-an-unspoken-but-key-role-in-telangana-elections%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Full%20Text%3A%20Pronab%20Sen%20Explains%20Why%20Data%20on%20Which%20GDP%20Is%20Calculated%20Is%20A%20Major%20Concern%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F12%2F06133536%2FKT-2-December-2021.00_46_11_06.Still002-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIndia%E2%80%99s%20former%20chief%20statistician%20Pronab%20Sen%20says%20that%20the%20data%20on%20which%20India%E2%80%99s%20GDP%20is%20calculated%20is%20%E2%80%9Ca%20major%20concern%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20if%20not%20corrected%20soon%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20GDP%20growth%20figures%20could%20become%20%E2%80%9Cunreliable%E2%80%9D.%20He%20says%20he%20believes%20the%20Q1%20GDP%20growth%20figure%20of%207.8%25%20is%20an%20overestimation.%20He%20believes%206.5%25%20is%20more%20accurate.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIn%20an%20interview%20with%20Karan%20Thapar%2C%20he%20explains%20why%20he%20believes%20the%20recent%20Periodic%20Labour%20Force%20Survey%20finding%20that%2058%25%20of%20the%20workforce%20are%20self-employed%20is%20not%20an%20indication%20of%20increasing%20self-entrepreneurship%20(as%20claimed%20by%20SBI%20economists)%20but%20distress%20employment.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20following%20is%20a%20transcript%20of%20the%20video%20interview%20that%20was%20published%20by%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Fwatch-karan-thapar-pronab-sen-gdp-figure-concern%5C%22%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fvideo%2Fwatch-karan-thapar-pronab-sen-gdp-figure-concern%5C%22%3E%20on%20November%2021%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It%20has%20been%20edited%20lightly%20for%20style%2C%20clarity%20and%20syntax.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EKaran%20Thapar%3A%20Hello%20and%20welcome%20to%20a%20special%20interview%20for%20The%20Wire.%20India%20pays%20a%20lot%20of%20attention%20to%20GDP%20and%20many%20people%20believe%20it%20accurately%20reflects%20the%20state%20of%20the%20economy.%20But%20does%20it%3F%20We%E2%80%99re%20going%20to%20answer%20that%20question%20by%20raising%20two%20further%20questions.%20First%20of%20all%2C%20how%20accurately%20does%20India%20calculate%20its%20GDP%3F%20And%20secondly%2C%20how%20meaningful%20is%20GDP%20for%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20the%20country%3F%20And%20remember%20the%20vast%20majority%20are%20poor.%20To%20answer%20those%20questions%20I%E2%80%99m%20now%20joined%20by%20India%E2%80%99s%20former%20chief%20statistician%20and%20the%20country%20director%20of%20the%20International%20Growth%20Centre%2C%20Pronab%20Sen.%20Professor%20Sen%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20start%20with%20a%20series%20of%20concerns%20about%20how%20India%20calculates%20GDP%20before%20I%20broaden%20the%20discussion.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWriting%20in%20Project%20Syndicate%2C%20Professor%20Ashoka%20Modi%20says%20that%20India%20calculates%20GDP%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20income%20from%20production%20rather%20than%20expenditure%20growth%20in%20quarter%201%20has%20been%20overestimated.%20He%20says%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20income%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%207.8%25%2C%20and%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20expenditure%20it%E2%80%99s%201.4%25.%20And%20if%20you%20take%20an%20average%20of%20the%20two%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%204.5%25.%20So%2C%20my%20first%20question%20is%2C%20does%20India%20calculate%20GDP%20in%20a%20way%20that%20exaggerates%20growth%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPronab%20Sen%3A%20No.%20There%20are%20three%20ways%20of%20calculating%20GDP%20%E2%80%93%20from%20production%2C%20from%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eincomes%2C%20and%20from%20expenditures.%20If%20you%20had%20perfect%20measurement%2C%20the%20three%20would%20give%20you%20exactly%20the%20same%20result.%20The%20problem%20is%20that%20different%20countries%20have%20data%20sources%20which%20enable%20them%20to%20use%20one%20or%20maybe%20two%20at%20most%20of%20these%20three%20approaches.%20In%20our%20case%2C%20we%20rely%20on%20the%20production%20approach%20because%20that%E2%80%99s%20where%20the%20data%20is%20the%20best.%20On%20income%2C%20we%20have%20practically%20no%20data%20because%20there%20is%20a%20very%20large%20informal%20workforce%20for%20whom%20getting%20income%20data%20is%20practically%20impossible%2C%20when%20you%E2%80%99re%20living%20on%20an%20hourly%20wage.%20So%20the%20income%20approach%20is%20out.%20The%20expenditure%20approach%20is%20also%20fairly%20difficult%20to%20do%20and%20there%20are%20large%20measurement%20errors%20there.%20So%20for%20us%2C%20given%20our%20data%20systems%2C%20given%20what%20we%20are%20able%20to%20capture%2C%20the%20production%20approach%20is%20the%20best.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ciframe%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F6lNkA_ZyRWI%3Fsi%3DWaQCYwRBockWBi_o%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%20data-mce-type%3D%5C%22bookmark%5C%22%3E%EF%BB%BF%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%20you%20disagree%20with%20professor%20Modi%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20disagree%20with%20him.%20Now%2C%20as%20far%20as%20the%20expenditure%20approach%20is%20concerned%2C%20the%20fact%20of%20the%20matter%20is%20that%20for%20all%20policy%20purposes%2C%20you%20need%20the%20data%20by%20the%20expenditure%20approach.%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20good%20enough%20for%20you%20to%20know%20which%20industries%20are%20producing%20more%20or%20less%20or%20whatever.%20It%E2%80%99s%20very%20important%20for%20you%20to%20know%20what%E2%80%99s%20happening%20to%20savings%2C%20what%E2%80%99s%20happening%20to%20investments%2C%20what%E2%80%99s%20happening%20to%20consumption%20and%20so%20on.%20All%20our%20policies%20hinge%20around%20that.%20So%20the%20way%20we%20do%20the%20GDP%20here%20is%20we%20use%20the%20production%20approach%20as%20the%20b%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eenchmark%2C%20and%20then%20we%20try%20to%20estimate%20the%20expenditure%20approach%20with%20whatever%20data%20we%20have%20%E2%80%93%20much%20of%20which%20comes%20from%20the%20production%20approach%2C%20by%20the%20way.%20And%20there%20will%20always%20be%20a%20gap%2C%20simply%20because%20the%20data%20on%20the%20expenditure%20approach%20is%20limited.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EThat%E2%80%99s%20what%E2%80%99s%20called%20the%20discrepancy.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%E2%80%99s%20what%E2%80%99s%20called%20the%20discrepancy.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20it%E2%80%99s%20shown%20under%20the%20expenditure%20approach%2C%20so%20the%20system%20says%20look%2C%20we%20can%E2%80%99t%20give%20you%20the%20exact%20expenditure%20approach%20information%2C%20this%20is%20the%20best%20approximation%20we%20could%20do.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EProfessor%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20doubts%20arise%20from%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20discrepancy%20he%20says%20is%20very%20large%20and%20therefore%20he%20believes%20that%20the%20calculation%20itself%20is%20faulty.%20You%E2%80%99re%20now%20explaining%20that%20the%20way%20India%20calculates%20GDP%20is%20the%20best%20way%20for%20the%20country%20given%20our%20circumstances%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20our%20data%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%A6and%20therefore%20you%20disagree%20with%20Professor%20Modi.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20do%20indeed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENow%2C%20a%20second%20concern%20about%20the%20way%20we%20have%20been%20recently%20calculating%20GDP%20comes%20from%20Arvind%20Subramanian%2C%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20former%20chief%20economic%20advisor%20and%20his%20colleague%20and%20co-writer%20Josh%20Felman.%20They%20say%20that%20because%20the%20wholesale%20price%20index%20is%20used%20as%20the%20GDP%20deflator%20%E2%80%93%20a%20figure%20which%20they%20call%20a%20derive%20number%2C%20not%20measured%20directly%20and%20which%20fluctuates%20widely%20%E2%80%93%20because%20of%20that%2C%20they%20say%20GDP%20growth%2C%20particularly%20in%20the%20last%20few%20quarters%2C%20has%20been%20exaggerated.%20They%20say%20the%20truth%20is%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20quoting%20them%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20economy%20is%20actually%20decelerating%20rapidly%20but%20that%E2%80%99s%20not%20reflected%20in%20the%20GDP%20figures.%E2%80%9D%20To%20what%20extent%20do%20you%20agree%20or%20disagree%20with%20this%20concern%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20is%20some%20justice%20to%20that.%20The%20wholesale%20price%20index%20is%20not%20really%20the%20appropriate%20price%20deflator.%20What%20we%20should%20be%20using%20is%20what%20is%20called%20the%20Producer%20Price%20Index%2C%20which%20is%20what%20the%20producers%20are%20getting.%20Because%20remember%2C%20the%20data%20that%20we%20are%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3Egetting%20is%20coming%20from%20the%20production%20units.%20So%20what%20is%20of%20concern%20is%20how%20much%20are%20the%20producers%20getting%20for%20the%20act%20of%20production.%20We%20don%E2%80%99t%20get%20that.%20What%20we%20are%20getting%20is%20the%20Wholesale%20Price%20Index%2C%20which%20is%20usually%20the%20second%20point%20of%20sale.%20So%20what%20the%20Wholesale%20Price%20Index%20will%20contain%2C%20over%20and%20above%20what%20the%20producer%20gets%2C%20are%20transport%20and%20trade%20margins.%20And%20both%20of%20these%20can%20vary%20quite%20substantially.%20You%20know%2C%20any%20movement%20in%20the%20global%20oil%20prices%20and%20it%20immediately%20gets%20reflected.%20So%2C%20yes%2C%20I%20think%20there%20is%20some%20justice%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%2C%20you%20would%20agree%20with%20Subramanian%20and%20Felman%20when%20they%20say%20that%20in%20the%20last%20few%20quarters%20%E2%80%93%20and%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20how%20many%20%E2%80%98few%E2%80%99%20is%20%E2%80%93%20but%20they%20say%20in%20the%20last%20few%20quarters%20growth%20has%20been%20exaggerated%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWell%2C%20if%20we%E2%80%99re%20making%20that%20argument%2C%20then%20the%20corollary%20to%20that%20is%20that%20the%20WPI%20is%20systematically%20underestimating%20inflation.%20That%20would%20be%20the%20logical%20%5Bconclusion%5D%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20how%20you%20are%20overestimating%20the%20GDP.%20If%20you%E2%80%99re%20underestimating%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhich%20means%20your%20nominal%20GDP%20is%20wrong.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%2C%20clearly%2C%20Felman%20and%20Subramanian%20have%20in%20their%20minds%20an%20inflation%20figure%20which%20is%20much%20higher.%20This%20I%20suspect%20is%20coming%20from%20the%20observation%20that%20over%20the%20last%20seven%20months%2C%20the%20Wholesale%20Price%20Index%20has%20been%20in%20the%20negative%20territory.%20There%E2%80%99s%20been%20deflation.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnd%20I%20think%20they%E2%80%99ve%20played%20around%20with%20CPI%20%5BConsumer%20Price%20Index%5D.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENow%20when%20they%20look%20at%20CPI%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20sub%206%25%2C%20so%20it%E2%80%99s%20come%20down%20quite%20a%20lot.%20But%20the%20WPI%20has%20moved%20very%2C%20very%20widely.%20Earlier%20we%20had%20a%20situation%20where%20the%20WPI%20was%20running%20at%20about%2013-14%25%2C%20the%20CPI%20was%20about%207-8%25%2C%20the%20CPI%20came%20down%20from%207-8%25%20to%205%25%20about%20and%20the%20WPI%20came%20down%20from%2014%25%20to%20minus%208%25.%20So%20that%E2%80%99s%20what%20they%E2%80%99re%20really%20talking%20about.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhich%20is%20why%20the%20use%20of%20the%20WPI%2C%20which%20fluctuates%20widely%20to%20quote%20their%20language%2C%20is%20an%20unreliable%20way%20of%20deflating%20GDP%20or%20a%20misleading%20way.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENo%2C%20it%20is%2C%20should%20we%20say%20an%20approximation.%20It%20is%2C%20I%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20say%20entirely%20inappropriate.%20The%20question%20that%20really%20needs%20to%20be%20asked%20is%20whether%20we%20are%20measuring%20the%20WPI%20properly.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20they%20say%20in%20fact%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20derived%20figure%20and%20is%20not%20measured%20directly%20and%20therefore%20they%E2%80%99re%20suggesting%20by%20the%20use%20of%20those%20two%20words%20that%20it%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20accurately%20measured.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENo%2C%20it%20isn%E2%80%99t%20actually%20a%20derived%20figure.%20The%20WPI%20is%20measured%20directly%2C%20there%20is%20a%20basket%20of%20goods%20and%20these%20prices%20are%20taken%20from%20the%20mandis%20and%20the%20wholesale%20markets.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnd%20yet%20you%20still%20do%20believe%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20measure%20of%20correctness%20in%20what%20they%20have%20concluded%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYes%2C%20they%20have.%20As%20I%20said%2C%20because%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20the%20appropriate%20price%20index.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%20then%20let%20me%20ask%20you%20this.%20If%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20measure%20of%20correctness%2C%20to%20use%20your%20phrase%2C%20in%20what%20Subramanian%20and%20Felman%20have%20concluded%2C%20that%20growth%20over%20the%20last%20few%20quarters%20has%20been%20exaggerated%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20actually%20as%20they%20say%20decelerating%20rapidly%20that%E2%80%99s%20not%20reflected%20in%20the%20GDP%20outcome.%20Yet%20you%20disagree%20with%20Ashoka%20Modi.%20Could%20not%20the%20same%20logic%20apply%20to%20Ashoka%20Modi%2C%20that%20he%20too%20has%20spotted%20%E2%80%93%20maybe%20his%20explanation%20is%20wrong%20%E2%80%93%20but%20he%20too%20has%20spotted%20a%20higher%20level%20of%20GDP%20than%20should%20be%20the%20case%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYes%2C%20but%20the%20arguments%20are%20a%20little%20different%20%E2%80%93%20substantially%20different.%20Now%2C%20you%20know%2C%20as%20I%20said%2C%20that%20Ashoka%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20case%20would%20have%20been%20stronger%20had%20he%20not%20made%20a%20statement%20in%20his%20piece%20saying%20that%20we%20should%20do%20what%20the%20Americans%20do%2C%20which%20is%20take%20an%20average%20of%20the%20two.%20That%20really%20is%20a%20cop-out.%20That%20assumes%20that%20the%20chances%20of%20error%20are%20equal%20in%20the%20two%20approaches.%20They%20have%20to%20be%20equal%20for%20that%20to%20work.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20the%20point%20that%E2%80%99s%20interesting%20is%20that%20you%20do%20agree%20that%20not%20just%20in%20the%20last%20quarter%20but%20over%20the%2