rong%3EA%20full%20allocation%20compared%20to%20the%20year%20before%20would%20have%20been%20probably%20utilised%20only%20up%20to%2050%25%20and%20therefore%20there%E2%80%99d%20be%20no%20questions%20raised%20about%20demand%20for%20MGNREGA%20going%20up.%20And%20similarly%2C%20you%E2%80%99re%20saying%2C%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20prime%20minister%20announced%20free%20food%20gain%20for%20800%20million%20people%20for%205%20years%20is%20not%20really%20a%20reflection%20of%20food%20hunger%20and%20therefore%20of%20distress.%20It%E2%80%99s%20actually%20political%20to%20seek%20votes.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYeah%2C%20I%20suspect%20so.%20Now%20here%E2%80%A6%20In%20both%20cases%2C%20these%20were%20political%20decisions.%20The%20first%20was%20the%20optics%20of%20the%20budget%20and%20the%20second%20was%2C%20you%20know%2C%20taking%20away%20a%20campaigning%20point%20from%20the%20opposition.%20But%20having%20said%20that%2C%20as%20I%20said%2C%20there%20is%20collaborative%20data%2C%20right%3F%20So%20if%20you%20are%20looking%20at%20the%20issue%20of%20whether%20MGNREGA%20is%20important%20or%20not%2C%20just%20look%20at%20the%20data%20of%20the%20number%20of%20people%20who%20have%20accessed%20MGNREGA%2C%20that%20has%20gone%20up.%20There%E2%80%99s%20no%20question%20about%20it.%20Second%20is%20look%20at%20the%20employment%20data%2C%20that%20has%20been%20coming%20out%20regularly.%20Unemployment%20is%20down%20but%20it%20is%20down%20essentially%20because%20people%20have%20gone%20into%20%E2%80%98self-employment%E2%80%99%20mostly%2C%20and%20casual%20work.%20So%20we%20are%20talking%20about%20people%20who%20are%20desperate%20to%20do%20something%20not%20because%20it%E2%80%99s%20remunerative.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELet%E2%80%99s%20then%20come%20to%20that%20because%20I%20think%20that%E2%80%99s%20another%20very%20important%20way%20of%20seeing%20whether%20GDP%20reflects%20the%20real%20reality%20for%20the%20poor%20of%20this%20country%20which%20is%20the%20majority%2C%20by%20comparing%20what%E2%80%99s%20happening%20to%20GDP%20alongside%20what%E2%80%99s%20happening%20to%20the%20changing%20character%20of%20employment.%20Before%20I%20come%20to%20that%2C%20let%20me%20just%20clarify%20one%20thing%20for%20the%20audience.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhere%20you%20and%20I%20%E2%80%93%20or%20rather%20where%20you%20disagreed%20with%20my%20questions%20%E2%80%93%20was%20when%20I%20said%20to%20you%20that%20the%20use%20of%20the%20allocation%20for%20MGNREGA%20in%206%20months%20which%20was%20intended%20for%20a%20year%20does%20not%20reflect%20distress%20it%20reflects%20the%20cutting%20of%20the%20allocation.%20Again%20where%20you%20questioned%20the%20question%20I%20raised%20was%20to%20do%20with%20the%20prime%20minister%20making%20grain%20available%20to%20800%20million%20for%205%20years%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20political%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20a%20reflection%20of%20distress.%20But%20where%20you%20agree%20with%20my%20question%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20simply%20pointing%20that%20out%20to%20the%20audience-%20when%20I%20said%20that%20the%207.8%25%20figure%20did%20not%20reveal%20the%20high%20unemployment%20which%20was%208%25%20of%20the%20time%20has%20shot%20up%20now%20to%20over%2010%25%20and%20it%20didn%E2%80%99t%20reveal%20that%20even%20in%20that%20first%20quarter%2C%20something%20like%2020%20million%20families%20%E2%80%93%20which%20is%20100%20million%20people%20%E2%80%93%20were%20dependent%20NREGA.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWell%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20take%20the%20employment%20%5Bdata%5D.%20What%20I%20did%20say%2C%20that%20is%20if%20you%20use%20the%20periodic%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Elabour%20force%20survey%2C%20unemployment%20actually%20was%206%25%20and%20it%20came%20down%20to%203%25%2C%20not%208%25%20going%20up%20to%2010%25.%20So%20we%20have%20a%20fundamental%20disagreement%20between%20two%20data%20sources%20CMIE%20versus%20the%20government.%20That%E2%80%99s%20right%20and%20that%20is%20something%20that%20one%20could%20discuss%20but%20that%20would%20become%20a%20technical%20discussion.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnd%20all%20I%E2%80%99ll%20say%20for%20the%20sake%20of%20the%20audience%20is%20in%20my%20conversations%20with%20Mahesh%20Vyas%2C%20who%20is%20the%20CEO%20of%20CMIE%2C%20he%20has%20always%20staunchly%20and%20rigorously%20and%20vigorously%20defended%20his%20outcome%20and%20he%20has%20good%20reasons%20for%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3Equestioning%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20figures.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELet%E2%80%99s%20come%20to%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20figures%2C%C2%A0%20because%20I%20think%20it%E2%80%99s%20important%20to%20ask%20yourself%2C%20does%20the%20truth%20or%20the%20extent%20of%20the%20truth%20that%20the%20GDP%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3Ereflects%20about%20the%20economy%20also%20coincide%20and%20corroborate%20with%20the%20changing%20character%20of%20employment%3F%20Now%20the%20recent%20periodic%20labour%20force%20survey%20shows%20that%20the%20percentage%20of%20people%20self-employed%20has%20increased%20from%2052%25%20in%202017-18%20to%2058%25%20in%202022-23.%20This%20raises%20the%20first%20question%3A%20how%20good%20is%20the%20quality%20of%20self-employment%3F%20Do%20these%20people%20actually%20earn%20a%20decent%2C%20proper%20wage%20or%20are%20they%20%3Cem%3Epakorawallas%3C%2Fem%3E%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENo%2C%20even%20worse.%20See%2C%20by%20and%20large%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20self-employment%20is%20what%E2%80%99s%20called%20distress%20employment.%20We%20have%20nothing%20to%20do%2C%20we%20take%20whatever%20little%20we%20have%2C%20we%20sit%20on%20the%20footpath%20and%20we%20try%20to%20sell%20it.%20So%20which%20is%20one%20of%20the%20reasons%2C%20if%20you%20really%20look%20at%20our%20own%20historical%20data%20on%20employment%2C%20we%E2%80%99ve%20never%20had%20high%20unemployment.%20It%20has%20always%20hung%20around%20the%202.5-3%25%20mark%2C%20where%20people%20who%20didn%E2%80%99t%20actually%20have%20jobs%20and%20a%20secure%20source%20of%20income%2C%20they%20were%20all%20self-employed.%20So%20self-employment%20in%20other%20countries%20is%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Etreated%20as%20essentially%20entrepreneurship%20being%20expressed%2C%20which%20is%20a%20good%20thing.%20Out%20here%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20desperation.%20So%20self-employment%20going%20up%20is%20not%20a%20good%20thing.%20Now%20this%20is%20where%20the%20disagreement%20over%20the%20employment%20rate%20becomes%20important.%20So%20when%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20shoots%20up%2C%20whether%20we%20go%20by%20CMIE%20or%20by%20PLFS%2C%20there%20is%20no%20dispute%20that%20it%20has%20gone%20up%20to%208-10%25.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EOkay%2C%20the%20question%20that%20should%20have%20been%20asked%20is%20why%20were%20these%20people%20sitting%20around%20without%20becoming%20self-employed%3F%20Because%20earlier%20days%2C%20they%20would%20have%20simply%20been%20on%20the%20street%20trying%20to%20peddle%20something%20or%20the%20other.%20It%20didn%E2%80%99t%20happen.%20They%20declared%20themselves%20as%20unemployed%2C%20why%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBecause%20there%20is%20MGNREGA%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENo%2C%20it%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20so%20much%20because%20it%20was%20MGNREGA.%20I%20think%20it%20was%20hope%20that%20this%20was%20transient%20and%20the%20jobs%20would%20come%20back.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnd%20they%20didn%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20be%20seen%20as%20unemployed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThey%20didn%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20be%20seen%20to%20be%20employed.%20So%20they%20were%20just%20basically%20waiting%20till%20the%20jobs%20came%20back.%20What%20the%20data%20is%20suggesting%20if%20you%20read%20it%20properly%20is%20that%20that%20hope%20has%20gone%20and%20those%20people%20who%20were%20sitting%20out%20and%20reporting%20themselves%20as%20unemployed%20now%20have%20become%20self-employed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20that%20self-employment%20is%20not%20really%20employment%20as%20you%20said%2C%20sitting%20on%20the%20street%2C%20peddling%20what%20they%20have.%20For%20us%20to%20consider%20them%20as%20employed%20when%20it%20is%20desperation%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3Eis%20to%20misuse%20the%20word%20employed.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENo.%20There%E2%80%99s%20a%20very%20technical%20definition%20for%20employed%20which%20is%20used%20and%20this%20is%20a%20definition%20which%20is%20given%2C%20this%20is%20an%20international%20definition%20which%20the%20ILO%20uses.%20In%20fact%2C%20not%20just%20uses%20insists%20that%20we%20follow%20it.%20So%20it%E2%80%99s%20an%20ILO%20definition%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20global%20definition%2C%20that%20definition%20is%20used%20in%20this%20context%20for%20everybody.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20I%20discover%20that%20even%20within%20that%20category%20of%20self-employed%2C%20which%20is%20now%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E58%25%20of%20the%20workforce%2C%20one-third%20it%20appears%20are%20unpaid%20workers.%20Santosh%20Malhotra%20has%20calculated%20that%20the%20number%20of%20unpaid%20workers%20was%2040%20million%20in%202017-18%20and%20it%E2%80%99s%20more%20than%20doubled%20to%2095%20million%20in%202022-23.%20So%20out%20of%20that%20category%20of%2058%25%20of%20the%20workforce%20who%20are%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3Eself-employed%2C%2095%20million%20actually%20are%20unpaid.%20Now%20they%E2%80%99re%20still%20considered%20under%20the%20system%20as%20employed%20but%20it%E2%80%99s%20meaningless%20to%20say%20that%20someone%E2%80%99s%20employed%20and%20they%E2%80%99re%20not%20earning%20anything!%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENo%2C%20let%20me%20again%20try%20and%20explain%20how%20this%20could%20work.%20So%2C%20supposing%20I%E2%80%99m%20a%20street%20side%20vendor.%20I%20was%20sitting%20there%20from%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20say%207%20o%E2%80%99clock%20in%20the%20morning%20till%207%20in%20the%20e%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Evening.%20Now%2C%20my%20brother%20who%20was%20working%2C%20has%20lost%20his%20job.%20He%20comes%20and%20sits%20with%20me%20and%20now%20I%20open%20the%20shop%20at%206%20am%20and%20I%20close%20at%2012%20at%20night.%20So%20we%20are%20earning%20something%20more%20simply%20because%20it%E2%80%99s%20staying%20over%20but%20the%20fact%20of%20the%20matter%20is%20that%20this%20person%20isn%E2%80%99t%20really%20being%20paid.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20part%20of%20my%20collection.%20A%20lot%20of%20this%20kind%20of%20thing%20is%20happening.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELet%20me%20put%20it%20like%20this.%20I%E2%80%99m%20going%20back%20now%20deliberately%20to%20that%20GDP%20figure%20of%207.8%25%20for%20quarter%201.%20When%20you%20look%20at%20that%20and%20you%20say%20to%20yourself%2C%20%E2%80%98Oh%20the%20economy%20is%20doing%20brilliantly%20we%E2%80%99re%20really%20growing%20at%20a%20pretty%20fast%20rate.%E2%80%99%20You%20aren%E2%80%99t%20aware%20that%20hidden%20behind%20that%20figure%20is%20that%2058%25%20of%20your%20workforce%20is%20self-employed%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20as%20you%20said%20are%20sitting%20on%20the%20street%20peddling%20what%20little%20they%20have%20and%20of%20that%2058%25%2C%2095%20million%20actually%20not%20even%20being%20paid.%20They%E2%80%99re%20like%20the%20brother%20in%20your%20story.%20This%20is%20where%20the%207.8%25%20figure%20if%20it%E2%80%99s%20presented%20to%20the%20country%20is%20proof%20that%20everything%20is%20doing%20well%2C%20and%20we%E2%80%99re%20sailing%2C%20actually%2C%20it%20misleads%20you.%20Because%20when%20you%20dig%20deeper%20or%20you%20go%20to%20other%20statistics%2C%20you%20suddenly%20discover%20that%2095%20million%20are%20unpaid.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAny%20data%20can%20be%20misused.%20All%20data%20is%20produced%20for%20a%20purpose.%20It%20measures%20something%20very%20specific.%20If%20you%20then%20start%20loading%20all%20kinds%20of%20value%20connotations%20to%20it%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20not%20the%20problem%20with%20the%20data%20problem%2C%20that%E2%80%99s%20the%20problem%20with%20you.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAbsolutely%2C%20and%20that%E2%80%99s%20really%20my%20purpose%20in%20this%20interview%20%E2%80%93%20to%20point%20out%20through%20these%20questions%20and%20your%20answers%20that%20when%20the%20GDP%20data%20on%20its%20own%20particularly%2C%20again%20that%207.8%25%20figure%2C%20is%20touted%20as%20proof%20that%20we%E2%80%99re%20doing%20and%20everything%20is%20fine%2C%20the%20country%20is%20swimming%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20improving.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20country%20is%20swimming%2C%20this%20is%20correct.%20The%20country%20as%20an%20entity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20many%20people%20in%20that%20country%2C%20up%20to%20perhaps%2058%25.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMaybe%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMaybe%20even%20more%20self-employed%20sitting%20on%20the%20pavement%2C%20selling%20what%20little%20wares%20they%20have%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20other%20category%20that%20PLFS%20tells%20you%20has%20gone%20up%20is%20casual%20labour%2C%20which%20is%20again%20a%20distress.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20other%20thing%20that%E2%80%99s%20gone%20up%2C%20is%20women%20who%20are%20unpaid%20workers%2C%20particularly%20in%20rural%20India.%20These%20are%20wives%20and%20sisters%20joining%20their%20husbands%20and%20brothers%20simply%20to%20lend%20a%20hand%20but%20not%20really%20earning%20anything.%20So%20the%20point%20I%E2%80%99m%20really%20making%20is%20that%20the%20more%20we%20tout%20the%20GDP%20growth%20figure%20%E2%80%93%20which%20politicians%20do%20%E2%80%93%20as%20proof%20that%20everything%20is%20fine%2C%20the%20more%20we%20actually%20deceive%20and%20mislead%20ourselves%20if%20you%20don%E2%80%99t%20add%20to%20that%20picture%20these%20other%20statistics%20about%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3Eemployment%20and%20distress.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELook%20Karan%2C%20who%20do%20you%20mislead%3F%20The%20point%20is%20a%20person%20who%E2%80%99s%20become%20unemployed%20or%20who%E2%80%99s%20had%20family%20members%20who%20have%20become%20unemployed%2C%20they%20are%20not%20misled.%20Who%20is%20being%20misled%3F%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20you%20and%20me%2C%20who%20know%20neither%20about%20what%E2%80%99s%20happening%20to%20the%20country%20as%20a%20whole%20or%20to%20what%20is%20happening%20to%20the%20poor.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELet%20me%20put%20it%20like%20this%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20who%20depend%20upon%20information%20from%20newspapers%20or%20television%20channels%20where%20those%20papers%20and%20channels%20fail%20to%20contextualise%20the%20information%20and%20tell%20the%20full%20story%2C%20will%20be%20the%20ones%20who%20are%20misled.%20They%20will%20say%2C%20%E2%80%98Oh%20the%20country%20is%20growing%20at%207.8%25%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20going%20to%20be%20growing%20at%209%25%20next%20year%2C%20everything%20is%20fine%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20new%20horizon%20opening%20for%20us%2C%20we%20will%20be%20a%20superpower.%E2%80%99%20The%20truth%20is%20look%20at%20other%20statistics%20%E2%80%93%20of%20employment%2C%20of%20unpaid%20work%2C%20of%20hunger%20%E2%80%93%20and%20you%20suddenly%20discover%20another%20story%20and%20that%20is%20the%20point%20I%E2%80%99m%20trying%20to%20make%2C%20that%20the%20single-minded%20focus%20that%20we%20have%20developed%20in%20the%20last%20eight-nine%20years%20on%20GDP%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20tell%20the%20full%20story.%20It%20tells%20a%20story%20but%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20tell%20the%20full%20s%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3Etory.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20is%20absolutely%20correct.%20It%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20tell%20the%20full%20story%2C%20but%20it%20does%20tell%20an%20important%20story%20in%20itself%2C%20okay%3F%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20we%20would%20feel%20any%20better%20if%20the%20GDP%20growth%20had%20been%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E3.8%25.%20I%20mean%20that%20would%20be%20pure%20schadenfreude%2C%20which%20is%20saying%20that%20the%20poor%20are%20not%20doing%20well%20at%20all%20but%20the%20rich%20aren%E2%80%99t%20doing%20very%20well%20either%2C%20right%3F%20That%E2%80%99s%20all%20it%20says.%20Out%20here%20what%20you%E2%80%99re%20saying%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20the%20poor%20are%20doing%20badly%20but%20the%20rich%20are%20doing%20very%20well%2C%20thank%20you.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EActually%2C%20what%20I%E2%80%99m%20saying%20is%20this%3A%20we%20need%20as%20a%20country%20to%20become%20aware%20of%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20GDP%20figure%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20tell%20the%20full%20story.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20correct.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAnd%20when%20you%E2%80%99re%20talking%20about%20the%20lives%20of%20the%20majority%20of%20your%20countrymen%2C%20it%20actually%20leaves%20out%20their%20story%20almost%20completely.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYeah%2C%20you%20need%20different%20indicators%20for%20that.%20And%20those%20are%20indicators%20which%20tell%20you%20how%20the%20GDP%20is.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%E2%80%99ll%20come%20to%20that%20in%20a%20moment%E2%80%99s%20time%20because%20I%20think%20that%E2%80%99s%20a%20very%20important%20next%20step%20but%20let%20me%20first%20put%20you%20a%20rebuttal%20of%20the%20points%20that%20you%20and%20I%20are%20making%20about%20the%20Periodic%20Labour%20force%20Survey%20figures.%20They%20come%20from%20economists%20in%20the%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%2C%20they%20say%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20quoting%20them%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20increase%20in%20the%20self-employed%20is%20wrongly%20interpreted%20by%20labour%20economists%20and%20others%20as%20a%20signal%20of%20shrinking%20employment%20opportunities.%E2%80%9D%20They%20add%2C%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%9CIndia%E2%80%99s%20labour%20market%20is%20undergoing%20a%20deep%20structural%20transformation%20with%20self%20entrepreneurship%20across%20all%20echelons%20and%20higher%20educational%20attainment%20emerging%20as%20key%20enablers.%E2%80%9D%20Do%20you%20agree%20with%20that%20or%20disagree%20with%20that%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20completely%20disagree%20with%20it.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECompletely%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAbsolutely.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIn%20fact%2C%20then%20let%20me%20ask%20you%20this.%20Can%20you%20describe%20the%20self-employed%20and%20remember%2C%20within%20that%20are%2095%20million%20who%20aren%E2%80%99t%20earning%20anything%20at%20all%E2%80%A6%20can%20you%20describe%20either%20of%20those%20categories%20as%20self-entrepreneurship%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOh%20there%20is%2C%20there%20are%20a%20lot%20of%20elements%20of%20that%2C%20right%3F%20Here%20is%20the%20question%3A%20the%20question%20is%20not%20whether%20India%20has%20a%20very%20large%20pool%20of%20entrepreneurs%20at%20all%20levels.%20There%20are%2C%20certainly.%20So%20we%E2%80%99ve%20had%20a%20large%20number%20of%20self-employed.%20The%20question%20is%20that%20the%20sudden%20increase%20that%E2%80%99s%20taken%20place%20in%20self-employment%20is%E2%80%A6%20and%20remember%20this%20has%20happened%20in%20a%20period%20of%20two%20or%20two-three3%20years.%20Is%20that%20a%20sign%20of%20sudden%20blossoming%20of%20entrepreneurship%20or%20is%20it%20distress%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%E2%80%99s%20your%20answer%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20answer%20is%20distress.%20Entrepreneurship%2C%20budding%20entrepreneurship%20is%20a%20process.%20It%20takes%20time%2C%20it%20moves%2C%20it%20will%20move%20slowly.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%20in%20other%20words%20what%20the%20SBI%20economists%20called%20a%20sign%20of%20self-entrepreneurship%20is%20actually%20better%20understood%20as%20a%20sign%20of%20distress.%20One%20other%20thing.%20The%20SBI%20is%20also%20that%20the%20guy%20who%20sits%20on%20the%20pavement%20selling%20the%20wares%20that%20he%20has%20is%20an%20entrepreneur.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20sense%2C%20he%20is.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20entrepreneurship%20in%20the%20sense%20in%20which%20we%20understand%20the%20word%20large%20industrialist%20setting%20up%20companies%20and%20making%20profits.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENo%2C%20no%2C%20or%20a%20small%20businessman%20setting%20up%20shop.%20The%20question%20that%20somebody%20should%20ask%20SBI%20is%2C%20would%20you%20lend%20that%20guy%20some%20money%3F%20If%20you%20think%20he%E2%80%99s%20a%20budding%20entrepreneur%2C%20the%20answer%20would%20be%20an%20emphatic%20no.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOkay%2C%20let%E2%80%99s%20then%20come%20to%20what%20are%20the%20statistics%20and%20indices%20that%20we%20should%20be%20paying%20attention%20to%20if%20we%20want%20to%20understand%20what%20is%20happening%20to%20the%20majority%20of%20our%20countrymen.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYeah.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAs%20I%20keep%20saying%2C%20the%20majority%20of%20our%20countrymen%20are%20poor.%20Praveen%20Chakravarti%20in%20an%20article%20that%20he%20wrote%20for%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%20and%20I%E2%80%99ll%20add%20for%20the%20audience%20he%E2%80%99s%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Congress%20party%20%E2%80%93%20said%20that%20India%20%E2%80%93%20and%20he%20was%20talking%20both%20about%20the%20country%20and%20the%20opposition%20bloc%20%E2%80%93%20should%20actually%20cease%20to%20focus%20on%20GDP%20numbers%20and%20instead%20they%20should%20look%20at%20two%20things%20the%20total%20number%20of%20jobs%20created%20in%20the%20economy%20and%20what%20he%20called%20median%20income%20growth.%20He%20said%20these%20are%20better%20measures%20of%20what%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3Ematters%20to%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20the%20Indian%20people.%20Would%20you%20agree%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETrue.%20But%20the%20point%20is%20that%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20data%20on%20incomes%20at%20all.%20So%20you%20can%E2%80%99t%20concentrate%20on%20the%20median%20income%20growth.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20probably%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20good%20data%20about%20the%20number%20of%20jobs%20created%20either.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20have%20some%20measure%20of%20it%2C%20yes%2C%20we%20do.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGood%20or%20bad%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWell%2C%20again%20you%20know%2C%20one%20would%20have%20to%20define%20the%20jobs.%20If%20you%20use%20the%20jobs%20in%20a%20generic%20sense%20of%20work%2C%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20think%20what%20he%E2%80%99s%20saying%20is%20correct%20because%20that%20would%20pick%20up%20distress%20work%20as%20well.%20Where%20I%20would%20agree%20with%20him%20is%20if%20he%20said%20if%20he%20uses%20the%20term%20%E2%80%98jobs%E2%80%99%20as%20saying%20regular%20paid%20employment.%20Not%20necessarily%20organised.%20It%E2%80%99s%20not%20necessarily%20organised%20but%20regular%20paid%20employment%2C%20a%20regular%20wage%20income.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAgain%2C%20the%2058%25%20self-employed%20were%20not%20featured%20in%20this%20category%20at%20all%20cause%20you%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20pick%20it%20up.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20these%20may%20be%20good%20categories%20to%20look%20at%20because%20they%20better%20reflect%20the%20condition%20for%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20our%20country%20but%20we%20simply%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20the%20data.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20this%20is%20a%20very%20sad%20conclusion.%20What%20would%20reflect%20the%20truth%20about%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20our%20country%2C%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20have%20the%20data%20to%20find%20out.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWell%2C%20you%20know%20income%20is%20notoriously%20difficult%20to%20measure%2C%20all%20right%3F%20Simply%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ebecause%20nobody%20wants%20to%20give%20that%20information%2C%20for%20a%20variety%20of%20reasons.%20Which%20is%20why%20we%20do%20collect%20data%20on%20consumption.%20Consumption%20data%20is%20easier%20to%20get%20and%20it%20is%20a%20proxy%20for%20income%20with%20the%20assumption%20that%20how%20much%20you%20spend%20depends%20on%20how%20much%20you%20earn.%20So%20using%20the%20consumption%20data%20is%20actually%20the%20only%20way%20we%20have.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20relatively%20direct%20proxy%2C%20we%20do%20know%20that%20there%E2%80%99s%20a%20relationship%20issue%20here%20which%20I%20can%20elaborate%2C%20if%20you%20like.%20But%20it%20gives%20you%20some%20sense%20as%20to%20how%20the%20distribution%20in%20the%20country%20is%20changing%20between%20the%20rich%20and%20the%20poor.%20The%20point%20is%20typically%20what%20happens%20because%20the%20rich%20have%20much%20higher%20savings%20consumption%20distribution%20is%20much%20more%20equal%20than%20income%20distribution%2C%20typically%20that%E2%80%99s%20the%20case.%20But%20it%20does%20give%20you%20a%20fairly%20good%20insight%20into%20what%E2%80%99s%20happening%20to%20the%20poor.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20this%20would%20also%20reflect%20something%20else.%20The%20increase%20in%20inequality%20that%20is%20taking%20place%20in%20the%20country%2C%20it%20does%20reflect%20that%20right%3F%20And%20if%20you%20look%20simply%20at%20what%E2%80%99s%20happening%20to%20car%20sales%20at%20one%20end%20and%20scooter%20sales%20at%20the%20other%2C%20scooters%20bought%20by%20the%20poor%2C%20their%20rate%20of%20growth%20is%20very%20low%2C%20cars%20bought%20by%20the%20rich%2C%20their%20rate%20of%20growth%20is%20exceeding%20year%20by%20year.%20That%20is%20one%20way%20of%20finding%20out%20what%20is%20happening%20to%20the%20majority%20of%20our%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cstrong%3Ecountry%2C%20a%20minority%20is%20doing%20exceptionally%20well%2C%20thank%20you%20very%20much.%20The%20majority%20is%20stalling%20at%20best%20or%20shrinking%20at%20worst.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYes%2C%20but%20you%20know%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20little%20sad%20when%20you%20have%20to%20depend%20on%20indicators%20of%20that%20kind.%20We%20should%20be%20getting%20regular%20household%20consumption%20expenditure%20data.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThis%20is%20again%20where%20our%20data%20lets%20us%20down%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYes.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20need%20to%20make%20an%20effort%20to%20get%20this%20data.%20Why%20aren%E2%80%99t%20we%20making%20that%20effort%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWell%2C%20we%20are%20making%20the%20effort.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20data%20collection%20is%20in%20the%20field%20at%20the%20moment%20as%20we%20speak.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOkay%2C%20so%20maybe%20in%20a%20year%E2%80%99s%20time%2C%20we%20will%20have%20better%20data.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHopefully.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELet%20me%20at%20this%20point%2C%20raise%20a%20concern%20raised%20by%20Raghuram%20Rajan%20earlier%20this%20month%20in%20November.%20He%20says%20we%20need%20to%20create%2070%20million%20jobs%20over%20the%20next%2010%20years%20and%20he%20says%20the%20rate%20of%20growth%20necessary%20for%20this%20is%208%20or%208.5%25.%20In%20fact%2C%20he%20adds%2C%20even%20at%207.5%25%20growth%2C%20only%202%2F3%20of%20the%20jobs%20problem%20will%20be%20solved.%20Would%20you%20agree%20that%20if%20employment%20is%20the%20main%20concern%20%E2%80%93%20and%20I%20imagine%2C%20for%20the%20majority%20of%20our%20country%20getting%20a%20job%20is%20probably%20the%20difference%20between%20life%20and%20death%3F%20So%20if%20employment%20is%20the%20main%20concern%2C%20not%20growing%20fast%20enough%20to%20create%20the%20jobs%20we%20need%20is%20the%20real%20problem.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20is%20and%20if%20you%20really%20read%20what%20Raghu%20is%20saying%2C%20he%E2%80%99s%20talking%20about%20seven%20million%20jobs%20being%20created%20in%20a%20year.%20So%20he%E2%80%99s%20really%20talking%20about%20educated%20employment.%20That%E2%80%99s%20only%20a%20part%20of%20the%20story.%20These%20are%20the%20jobs%20we%20need%20to%20generate%20to%20employ%20people%20who%20are%20getting%20educated.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20take%20into%20account%20the%20jobs%20we%20need%20for%20everyone%20else.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEveryone%20else%20who%20is%20down%20there%2C%20who%20are%20in%20fact%20the%20poorest%20of%20the%20poor.%20The%20guys%20who%20are%20not%20finishing%20their%20class%20five.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThis%207%20million%20won%E2%80%99t%20cater%20for%20the%2058%25%20self-employed.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECorrect.%20If%20you%20take%20those%20into%20account%2C%20there%E2%80%99s%20another%205%20million%20of%20them%20waiting.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThis%20leads%20Professor%20Sen%20to%20two%20last%20questions%20before%20I%20end%20the%20interview%20and%20they%20are%20questions%20that%20I%20will%20admit%20disturb%20me.%20If%20we%E2%80%99re%20not%20creating%20enough%20jobs%20not%20just%20to%20meet%20Raghuram%20Rajan%E2%80%99s%20target%20of%207%20million%20a%20year%2C%20which%20is%20questionable%20whether%20we%20can%20achieve%20it%2C%20but%20to%20provide%20jobs%20for%20the%2058%25%20that%20are%20self-employed.%20If%20we%E2%80%99re%20not%20creating%20enough%20jobs%2C%20is%20there%20a%20danger%20that%20what%20we%20fondly%20call%20the%20demographic%20dividend%20could%20turn%20into%20a%20demographic%20predicament%20and%20perhaps%2C%20God%20forbid%2C%20at%20some%20point%20a%20demographic%20disaster%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWell%2C%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20whether%20it%20should%20be%20a%20demographic%20disaster.%20But%20what%20it%20certainly%20will%20be%20is%20an%20enormous%20opportunity%20lost.%20The%20demographic%20dividend%20is%20really%20about%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Epotential%20and%20if%20we%20miss%20it%2C%20future%20generations%20are%20going%20to%20hold%20us%20culpable.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20also%20if%20we%20miss%20it%2C%20we%20will%20soon%20become%20a%20country%20where%20we%20will%20be%E2%80%A6%20much%20older%20and%20therefore%20unable%20to%20produce.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYou%20will%20become%20a%20country%20where%20a%20very%20very%20large%20number%20of%20self-employed.%20We%20will%20be%20self-employed%2C%20we%E2%80%99%20be%20sitting%20there.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%2C%20India%20has%20a%20great%20future%20for%20pakorawalas.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20trinkets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESo%2C%20in%20other%20words%2C%20my%20phrase%20demographic%20predicament%20sounds%20increasingly%20correct.%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWell%2C%20yes.%20But%20as%20I%20said%2C%20it%20is%20a%20problem%2C%20it%20will%20be%20a%20source%20of%20frustration%20but%20the%20most%20important%20thing%20is%20that%20it%20will%20be%20such%20a%20waste%20of%20an%20opportunity.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F14193052%2FKT-28-March-2022.00_38_57_04.Still003final.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F14193052%2FKT-28-March-2022.00_38_57_04.Still003final.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F14193052%2FKT-28-March-2022.00_38_57_04.Still003final-300x171.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F14193052%2FKT-28-March-2022.00_38_57_04.Still003final-1024x582.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-668104%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22682%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ERaghuram%20Rajan.%20Photo%3A%20The%20Wire%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYes%20and%20there%E2%80%99s%20something%20else%20that%20follows%20from%20it.%20Will%20we%20become%20a%20developed%20country%3F%20The%20prime%20minister%20has%20taken%20to%20repeating%20as%20often%20as%20he%20can%20that%20we%20will%20be%20a%20developed%20country%20by%202047.%20Now%20by%20World%20Bank%20standards%2C%20developed%20countries%20I%20believe%20have%20per%20capita%20incomes%20of%20%2413%2C200.%20If%20you%20want%20to%20peg%20yourself%20to%20the%20United%20Kingdom%2C%20a%20country%E2%80%99s%20economy%20we%20overtook%20a%20couple%20of%20months%20maybe%20at%20the%20most%20a%20year%20ago%2C%20we%20need%20to%20have%20a%20per%20capita%20income%20of%20%2445%2C000.%20Our%20per%20capita%20income%20at%20the%20moment%20is%20%242%2C388.%20So%2C%20given%20the%20way%20things%20are%20progressing%2C%20will%20we%20be%20a%20developed%20country%20in%202047%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20if%20the%20definition%20is%20%2413%2C200%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20if%20we%20want%20to%20be%20at%20the%20level%20of%20the%20United%20Kingdom%20and%20America-%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENo%2C%20no%2C%20no%2C%20no%2C%20not%20even%20close.%20But%20the%20real%20question%20then%20is%20what%20you%20had%20raised%20earlier.%20Is%20%2413%2C200%20%E2%80%93%20taking%20the%20GDP%2C%20dividing%20by%20the%20population%E2%80%A6%20That%E2%80%99s%20what%20per%20capita%20income%20means.%20It%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20say%20anything%20about%20how%20it%20is%20distributed.%20So%2C%20if%20the%20distribution%20continues%20to%20get%20worse%2C%20then%20we%20may%20well%20reach%20%2413%2C200%20and%20still%20have%20masses%20of%20unemployed%20people%20and%20massive%20poverty.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYou%E2%80%99re%20making%20two%20very%20important%20points.%20First%20of%20all%2C%20if%20the%20prime%20minister%20means%20we%E2%80%99ll%20be%20a%20developed%20country%20that%20we%20will%20be%20at%20the%20same%20per%20capita%20income%20level%20of%20the%20UK%20or%20the%20US%20or%20France%20or%20Germany%2C%20the%20answer%20is%20absolutely%20flatly%20no%20we%20won%E2%80%99t.%20But%20if%20he%20says%20that%20we%20can%20meet%20the%20much%20lower%20world%20back%20standard%20of%20%2413%2C200%20which%20is%20if%20I%E2%80%99ve%20got%20my%20mathematics%20correct%2C%20just%20about%20above%20a%20quarter%20of%20the%20UK%20level%2C%20that%20we%20can%20achieve.%20In%20other%20words%2C%20by%202047%20we%E2%80%99ll%20be%20developed%20by%20World%20Bank%20standards%20but%20we%E2%80%99ll%20still%20be%20only%20a%20quarter%20of%20what%20the%20UK%20is%E2%80%A6%20and%20by%20the%20way%2C%20the%20UK%2C%20by%20then%2C%20will%20have%20probably%20shot%20up%20to%20%2450%2C000%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20don%E2%80%99t%20know.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20other%20danger%20is%20that%20even%20at%20the%20%2413%2C200%20per%20capita%20income%20level%20if%20we%20reach%20it%20in%202047%2C%20we%20could%20still%20have%20a%20situation%20where%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20could%20be%20self-employed%20and%20maybe%20another%20100-odd%20million%20still%20in%20that%20dreadful%20predicament%20of%20self-employed%20but%20not%20earning%20anything.%20That%20means%20that%20as%20far%20as%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20country%20is%20concerned%20and%20I%20keep%20saying%20they%E2%80%99re%20poor%2C%20their%20future%20at%20the%20moment%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20look%20particularly%20rosy%20at%20all.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWell%2C%20no.%20We%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20everything%20depends%20upon%20what%20we%20do%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20way%20we%20develop%20the%20economy.%20So%2C%20if%20we%20have%20the%20trend%20that%20we%20have%20seen%20over%20the%20last%20five-six%20years%20where%20the%20bulk%20of%20the%20growth%20has%20been%20concentrated%20in%20the%20organised%20sector%20of%20the%20economy%E2%80%A6%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThen%20this%20lot%20are%20forgotten%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20lot%20are%20forgotten%20and%20it%20is%20getting%20worse.%20The%20gap%20was%20increasing%20and%20we%E2%80%99ve%20talked%20about%20this%20before.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBut%20you%E2%80%99re%20saying%20a%20very%20important%20thing.%20If%20we%20continue%20the%20way%20we%20have%20for%20the%20last%20five-six%20years%2C%20the%20future%20for%20the%20poor%20and%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20country%20will%20remain%20bleak%20and%20dark.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20is%20correct.%20So%20we%20really%20need%20to%20look%20at%20our%20development%20strategy.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThat%20is%20a%20subject%20for%20another%20day%2C%20I%20promise%20I%20will%20come%20back%20to%20you%20and%20talk%20about%20that.%20But%20the%20picture%20I%20want%20to%20leave%20the%20audience%20with%20is%20this%2C%20and%20correct%20me%20if%20I%E2%80%99m%20wrong.%20Any%20single-minded%20focus%20on%20GDP%20as%20a%20way%20of%20telling%20the%20country%20and%20the%20world%20all%E2%80%99s%20well%2C%20we%E2%80%99re%20swimming%20fails%20to%20convey%20the%20reality%20faced%20by%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20country%20who%20are%20poor.%20Secondly%2C%20if%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20change%20our%20development%20strategy%20but%20continue%20the%20way%20we%20have%20for%20the%20last%20five-six%20years%2C%20then%20the%20future%20for%20the%20majority%20who%20are%20poor%20remains%20bleak%20and%20even%20if%20we%20reach%20in%202047%20the%20%2413%2C200%20per%20capita%20income%20levels%20and%20therefore%20technically%20qualified%20to%20be%20a%20developed%20country%2C%20we%20could%20still%20have%2058%25%20self-employed.%20Within%20which%20100%20million%20are%20actually%20not%20earning%20anything%20at%20all.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20a%20depressing%20end.%20Thank%20you%20very%20much%20indeed!%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYou%E2%80%99re%20welcome!%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701263459000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F12%2F06133536%2FKT-2-December-2021.00_46_11_06.Still002-1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fkaran-thapar-pronab-sen-gdp-data-transcript%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20an%20interview%20with%20Karan%20Thapar%2C%20he%20says%20the%20Q1%20GDP%20growth%20figure%20of%207.8%25%20is%20an%20overestimation%20and%20the%20actual%20figure%20is%20around%206.5%25.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fkaran-thapar-pronab-sen-gdp-data-transcript%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Who%20is%20attending%20COP28%3F%20Leaders%2C%20royalty%20and%20billionaires%20on%20invite%20list%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701261780000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F23%2F11%2F768x432%2Fskynews-gates-king-kerry_6377012.png%3F20231129213940%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fwho-is-attending-cop28-leaders-royalty-and-billionaires-on-invite-list-13018862%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22More%20than%20160%20world%20leaders%20are%20expected%20to%20attend%20the%20COP28%20climate%20summit%2C%20which%20begins%20in%20Dubai%20today.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fwho-is-attending-cop28-leaders-royalty-and-billionaires-on-invite-list-13018862%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fwho-is-attending-cop28-leaders-royalty-and-bill